title: tiramisu
directions: Line a 2 1/2-quart trifle bowl with 1 package of ladyfingers that have been brushed with 1/3 cup coffee liquor, 2 teaspoons Espresso powder, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon water.

title: hamburger-eggplant casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
When meat is brown and celery and onion are tender, drain off excess grease.
Season with salt and pepper.
Peel and dice into small cubes eggplant. Cook diced eggplant in salted, boiling water.
Bring back to boil and cook until tender.
Drain.
Combine cooked, drained eggplant with cooked meat mixture and add ketchup, mix.
Cover bottom of buttered casserole dish generously with cracker crumbs.
Add meat mixture and top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 375° over for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Then add 1/2 cup catsup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta with soy sauce
directions: Mix soy sauce and garlic.
Blend the mixture to the cooked pasta.
Serve alone or as a side dish with meat or stir-fry vegetables.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Place cast-iron skillet in a 475° oven until skillet is hot.
When skillet is heated, spoon in mixture and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve hot, buttered.

title: touchdown dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine ingredients; stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers or assorted vegetables.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick according to directions on box for rolled biscuits.
Roll into rectangle, approximately 1/4-inch thick. Spread with mixture of combined ham, peas and egg.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch circles and place slices on greased cookie pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with your favorite hot cheese sauce. Makes approximately 8 to 10 slices.

title: aunt mae's refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix in bowl salt, onions, cucumbers and peppers; let stand 1 hour; drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Pour over cucumber mixture and refrigerate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add vanilla, then flour, a little at a time, until all flour is used.
Add nuts and chips; stir.
Roll into small balls and flatten on an ungreased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 16 minutes.

title: super chocolate cookies(very, very good!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter and brown sugar.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture and mix well. Stir in Nestle morsels, Macadamia nuts and coconut.
Drop by well rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Allow to stand for 2 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Remove stems from tomatoes.
Place tomato stem-side-down.
Cut almost through each tomato to form 6 wedges.
Divide lettuce among 4 serving plates.
Top with tomato, separating wedges slightly to form cup shape.
Set aside.
Crumble ground beef into 1-quart glass casserole; add onion.
Microwave on Full power, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes or until meat is set, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in chili sauce, garlic salt and peppers.
Cover with casserole lid. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes on Full power until heated through. Spoon meat mixture into center of each tomato.
Top with cheese, taco chips and taco sauce.
Serve with sour cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare tortilla shells.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain. Stir in water, chili powder, salt, garlic powder, red pepper and kidney beans.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool 10 minutes.
Mix lettuce, cheese, olives, tomatoes and onion in large bowl.
Toss with dressing.
Pour ground beef mixture over top and toss.
Divide among tortilla shells.
Garnish with avocado and sour cream. Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach or broccoli bake
directions: Cook rice; cook vegetables.
Saute celery and onion with butter.
Mix all together in a covered bowl; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until heated through.

title: raisin mint relish for lamb
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine raisins, onion, apple juice and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until most of the liquid is reduced.
Stir in spearmint and salt. Simmer 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
This can be packed in small jars and given as gifts!

title: veggie bars
directions: Using 11 x 17-inch baking pan, lay rolls by pressing edges together.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°, no longer, and cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Mix together. Spread mixture over roll crust to edges and cool.
Sprinkle with chopped mixed veggies and cover with Saran Wrap.
Push veggies into cream cheese mixture.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: holly smoke
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9 x 2 in. pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Mix next 2 ingredients well.
Fold in cool whip. spread over cooled crust.
Mix final 2 ingredients and spread over top of second layer.
Top with cool whip and chopped pecans. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken quarters, garlic, oregano, pepper, salt, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers and bay leaves. Cover and let marinate, refrigerated, overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Combine
peppers,
tomatoes, onions and vinegar in bowl of food
processor
or
blender and chop well to blend or chop them by hand.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together while potatoes are still warm.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Fold into potato mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients; heat.
Take 1 can butterflake biscuits and roll thin as possible.
Cut in strips and drop in hot mixture.
Simmer until dumplings are done.
Serve warm.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add eggs and butter.
Beat slowly until well mixed.
Add cream.
Bake in 2 unbaked crusts at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat crusts before filling is put in.

title: switchel
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring to dissolve sugar. Chill and serve with ice.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Mix together in bowl next 6 ingredients.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
4 noodles on bottom; 1/2 of cheese-egg mixture; 1 package Mozzarella cheese; meat sauce and repeat.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: lincoln logs
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add condensed milk and chocolate chips.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Push into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: carrot cookie bars
directions: Blend margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and carrots. Beat until smooth. Combine dry ingredients and stir into carrot mixture. Fold in raisins. Spread dough in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until done and lightly browned. Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting. Cut into squares.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown in a little oil; drain or pat excess oil from steak.
Add all of the other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours or until steak is fork-tender.

title: summer chicken salad sandwiches
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, scallions, parsely adn pecans.
In a cup, combine the yogurt, mayonnaise and curry. Mix the dressing with the chicken.
Divide the chicken among the rolls.
Place a nectarine slice in each sandwich.
Serves 6.
Per serving:
346 calories, 9 grams fat (24% of calories), 54.8 milligrams cholesterol, 405 mg. sodium, 4.9 g. dietary fiber.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Rub in the shortening lightly.
Beat egg and add with milk.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush over with melted utter and bake in a moderate oven.

title: rhonda's sugar cookies
directions: Mix the above together and then combine with creamed mixture. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip into granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about four dozen cookies.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add ketchup and mix together.
Add crab and horseradish to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour before using.
This is a dip for raw vegetables.

title: pork chops incredible
directions: Dredge chops in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Brown in large skillet.
Place browned chops in crock-pot.
Mix soups in skillet and pour over chops.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours, high 3 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour in graham craker crust.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix in evening and chill. Bake next day.
Roll thick.

title: freezer fudge
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased pan and freeze 1/2 hour.

title: hash brown breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add milk. Melt butter in pan, 9 x 13. Arrange hash browns in pan. Put ham and cheese over hash browns. Pour egg mixture over all and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: no name cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 layer cake pans.
When cooled, place layers in freezer about 30 minutes.
When slightly frozen, split each layer, carefully cutting thru horizontally. Start with a bottom piece, then add a layer of Cool Whip, then another layer of cake.
Then spread frosting, add another layer of cake, then Cool Whip, then the last layer of cake and top with frosting.
Refrigerate for several hours - do not cut until firm.

title: ginger ale-nectar punch
directions: Combine first five ingredients and chill.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over ice.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Make cake according to box.
Bake in 11 x 17 x 1-inch pan for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, mix 1 cup Pet milk, marshmallows and 1 cup sugar.
Heat until marshmallows are almost melted (a little lumpy).
Add coconut and spread on hot cake.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer all ingredients 1 hour and serve warm.

title: aunt laura's mints
directions: Stir with spoon the first 4 ingredients.
Separate mint dough into 2 bowls.
Add different food coloring into each bowl; mix well with hands.
Press mints out using cookie press (hard job requires strength).
Press mints onto waxed paper and set aside to dry for 24 hours.
You will have beautiful red and green (or use pastel colors) mints for a party.

title: tiny tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. For pastry, in a mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter and cream cheese until thoroughly combined. Stir in flour. Press a rounded teaspoonful of pastry evenly into the bottom and up the sides of each of 24 ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups. Fill each pastry-lined muffin cup with about 1 heaping teaspoonful of desired filling. Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes or until pastry is golden and filling is puffed. Cool slightly in the pan, then remove and cool completely on a wire rack. Makes 24.

title: hawaiian macaroni salad(dessert)
directions: Separate fruit from juice.
Save both while cooking macaroni. Prepare the fruit sauce.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, eggs and juice in saucepan.
Cook to a boil; remove from heat.
The sauce will thicken as it cools.
Mix sauce with drained macaroni in a large bowl.
Mix well and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight. Next day, fold in fruit, marshmallows and topping.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 6 quarts.
Good for a crowd.

title: french onion dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: a tavern dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough oil to make a smooth paste. Then add vinegar, oil and eggs alternately whipping after each addition to form a liquid.

title: pineapple party punch
directions: Chill juices.
In large punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, cranberry juice, lemonade concentrate, sugar and food coloring. Just before serving, pour in ginger ale.
Garnish with ice ring or serve over ice.

title: microwave butter pecan ice cream pie
directions: Place butter in
4-cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in flour, half of the pecans and sugar; mix well.
Press mixture firmly onto bottom and sides of 9-inch microproof pie plate.
Cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating halfway through cooking time.
Cool to room temperature. Spoon ice cream into shell (if ice cream is very firm, place carton on microproof plate; cook on 30 for 2 minutes or until softened).
Sprinkle remaining pecans over top.
Freeze until firm.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spread in 9-inch pie or quiche dish. Bake 15 minutes.
Stir after 8 minutes.
Garnish with additional almonds.
Serve with crackers.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and nuts.
Spread mixture on a slice of ham, then roll it up.
For best results, place the ham rolls in the refrigerator for a little while before slicing.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Spoon a small amount of spaghetti sauce in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Place a layer of pasta, a layer of beef and a layer of cottage cheese. Continue to layer in this manner until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of sauce.
Cover tightly and bake in a 325° oven until pasta is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
When pasta is tender, uncover and place a layer of Mozzarella cheese slices on top.
Replace in oven until cheese melts.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup coconut, sour cream, crushed pineapple (save juice) and sugar.
Mix and let stay in refrigerator overnight. Use cake mix as directed, except omit 1/4 cup water.
Add 1/4 cup pineapple juice. Bake.
Cool.
Put icing on cake and add rest of coconut on top and sides.
Very good.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. A great way to use up that Thanksgiving turkey.

title: mexican chicken tortilla pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place tortillas on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp but not brown. Spread 1/4 bean dip over each tortilla.
Top with 1/4 of chicken, olives, onions, pimento and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with guacamole. Yields 4 pizzas.

title: chocolate peanut butter truffles
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter and stir until smooth.
Add condensed milk and vanilla.
Cook and stir until thickened and well blended, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts, cocoa, graham cracker crumbs or confectioners sugar.
Chill until firm about 1 hour.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: jello pudding fudge
directions: Combine pudding mix, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to full boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly blend in sugar and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and cool.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts for nut mixture.
Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Mix the flour mixture with the sour cream.

title: perfect hard-boiled eggs
directions: Add just enough water to a saucepan to cover the eggs.
Bring water to a boil and immediately remove saucepan from heat.
Cover and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Plunge eggs into cold water and peel immediately.
This will prevent eggs from blackening.
It also guarantees tender, non-rubbery whites and centered yolks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and use as a dip with any variety of fruit.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Mix together, bake at 325 degrees in 8 x 8-inch greased pan set in pan of hot water for 45 minutes.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Hollow out one loaf of bread; cut center and second loaf into dipping pieces.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour dip into hollow bread to serve and surround with dipping pieces.
Dip may be made ahead and kept refrigerated in a bowl overnight.

title: chocolate oat cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in sugars and margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to oat mixture.
Stir in 1/2 bag of chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour batter into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining chips and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding with buttermilk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Break cookies into dime-sized pieces and fold into mixture.
Refrigerate.
Marshmallows and bananas may be used.
You cannot taste the buttermilk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients.
Sift together next 5 ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheerios nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Heat brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy and light colored.
Pour over cereal mixture in 4-quart bowl.
Stir until coated.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Stir; let stand just until cool (about 10 minutes).
Loosen mixture with spatula.
Let stand until firm (about 30 minutes). Break into bite-size pieces.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: mint-marshmallow sauce
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, cut in small pieces, and stir until melted.
Add marshmallow-sugar-water mixture gradually to stiffly beaten egg white.
Flavor, color and chill before serving.

title: karin's hot sauce
directions: Put half of the ingredients in blender; the other half in a large jar.

title: pork and beans
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
While the beans are draining, brown cubed pork and remove from pan.
Add butter, onion and green pepper.
Saute.
Add beans, pork, ketchup, barbecue sauce, sugar and molasses.
Cook over low heat for about 30 minutes and serve. If sauce gets too dry, add more ketchup, barbecue sauce or water.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Flour and brown chicken, using a little salt or Lawry's salt. In 9 x 13-inch pan, combine rice, both cans of soup and water. Lay
the chicken in it and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
While it's melting, mix together all other ingredients.
Pour butter into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: see's rocky road fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
After mixture comes to a boil, continue to stir constantly for 9 minutes, while boiling.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow whip and chocolate chips, butter and vanilla. Beat until it dissolves.
Add nuts; mix.
Pan it in buttered pan. Let it sit for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: caramel apple bars
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, oats and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Set aside 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, put oil, bacon bits and onions; cook until onions are tender, then add potatoes, corn, 1 1/2 cans chicken broth, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Combine the 1/2 can broth and flour; strain into the pot and stir until it thickens.
Reduce heat to low and stir in buttermilk.
Heat but do not boil.
Top each bowl with bacon bits.
Makes approximately 6 servings.
If it gets too thick, add more buttermilk.

title: mix and store pie crust mix
directions: Mix together flour, shortening and salt for 2-crust pie. Measure out 2 1/4 cups mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Chill 1/4 cup water before adding to measured mixture.
Let crust rest before rolling out.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put beef in bottom of casserole.
Roll chicken in bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place on beef portions.
Fold sour cream in mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo. Sprinkle this mixture over all of the ingredients.
Use a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Put biscuits into bag and shake.
Put coated biscuits in greased tube cake pan.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Pour this mixture over biscuits.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Break into pieces when cool.
Monkey see, monkey do.

title: caramel devils food cake
directions: No mixer needed for this recipe. Just stir ingredients together with spoon. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: tang pie
directions: Thoroughly mix Tang with condensed milk; stir in sour cream, then the nondairy topping.
Mix well. Divide between the 2 crusts and chill thoroughly in the refrigerator.
Freezes well.
Thaw about 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook all vegetables and juice until vegetables are almost done.
Drop bouillon cubes in pot while boiling.
Add chicken which has been cooked and cut into chunks.
In a separate pot, cook egg noodles until done; drain and add to soup.
Season as desired with salt and pepper.
Good with crackers or by itself. Enjoy!

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Milk or water can be added if texture is too thick.
The longer you beat, the fluffier it will become.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Add onion and green pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Lightly saute beef and onion; add remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes at the very last.
Serve with toasted cheese bread.
Super cheap, easy and very hearty.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and soda. Set aside.
Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture a little at a time.
Add zucchini and nuts or raisins.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cinnamon brownies
directions: In bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Stir in peanut butter.
Spread in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13 in. pan in this order, lettuce, peas, celery and onion.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Ice completely with Miracle Whip.
Crumble the broiled bacon on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese generously over the bacon.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: moist chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine, gradually add sugar and beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together, alternately with syrup; blend well.
Add nuts and vanilla and pour into a 9-inch tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until sides start to pull away from pan.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken and spinach with cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Add spinach and Ricotta cheese; sprinkle in Parmesan cheese and pepper and parsley.
Mix all together and stir in frying pan. When mixture is at pick-up consistency, roll in chicken breast. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: louisiana rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Meanwhile, cook rice.
Combine with the sauce.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger steak
directions: To ground beef, add the onion, cracker crumbs and egg; mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make into 4 burgers. Cook until done.
Make gravy and add burgers to gravy.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: naomi's tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Cool and place in casserole dish.
Pour Tater Tots on top of meat.
Mix soups and a small amount of milk and pour over Tater Tots.
Put onion rings on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon delights
directions: Combine angel food cake mix and lemon pie filling and mix well.
Spray a 13x9 inch baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Pour mixture inside and spread out evenly.
Top with almonds and coconut and bake for 30 minutes at 350°F.
Allow to cool before cutting into squares.

title: tag casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions.
Add corn (drained), tomato sauce and noodles.
Use skillet you browned in or use electric skillet.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve while hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soak the shrimp in lemon juice for 1 hour.
Cream together the remaining ingredients.
Add shrimp and chill.
Use as dip for carrots or celery.
Also good with crackers.

title: low-fat applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.
In a mixer bowl, combine sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixed well.
Add applesauce and flour mixture alternately to egg mixture at low speed.
Stir in raisins.
Turn into pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve with vegetables and/or assorted crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot and spicy jerky
directions: Cut venison into 1/4-inch strips.
Combine ingredients for marinade.
Marinate venison for 24 hours.
Place toothpicks through ends of strips.
Hang on rack in oven.
Place rack on highest setting.
Set oven at 150°.
Bake 4 to 6 hours.

title: polly ann's potato salad
directions: Peel and halve potatoes and slice.
Add eggs, celery, mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and blend thoroughly.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Sprinkle all over the paprika and garnish with parsley.

title: refrigerator rolls(no knead)
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar and salt to about 1/2 of the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and Wesson oil.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed and shape into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet, cover and let rise until light (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Heat oven to 400° and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for 3 or 4 days.

title: crock-pot venison roast
directions: Place roast under water frozen.
Sprinkle with seasonings to taste.
Place in crock-pot with soy and Worcestershire sauces. Fill with water to approximately 1 inch above roast.
Cook on low for at least 16 hours.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Add almonds, which have been shaved.
Mix well.
Form into rolls.
Freeze, slice and bake in a moderate 350° oven.
Keeps well and are delicious.

title: midge's macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper, onion, catsup and steak sauce together. Add tomatoes; cook slowly 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Mix with beef mixture.
Fold in mushroom soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.
Two quart baking dish is fine for recipe.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour your cake pan. Beat eggs first, then add vanilla, salt, baking soda, sugar and Crisco.
Mix until well blended.
Add flour and buttermilk and mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hour (oven time may vary).

title: mama's sour chow chow
directions: You may use tomatoes just beginning to ripen.

title: mexicali pizza wheel
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and garlic until brown; drain. Add kidney beans, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Roll dough to 15-inch circle; place on greased pan. Form standing rim of dough around edge.
Cut x in center to form 8 wedges in center.
Spread mixture evenly on dough; sprinkle with cheese, pimientos and chilies.
Pull cut points of dough over filling; tuck under rim.
Bake at 425° on low rack for 20 minutes.

title: carm's lemon glaze cake
directions: While still warm, poke cake with holes.
Pour glaze over and spread.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
Cream butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking soda to sour cream. Add flour, one cup at a time, and sour cream, 1/3 at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: imperial crab
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in shells and top each with 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 425° oven 15 to 20 minutes (until golden brown on top).

title: brussels sprouts and walnut au gratin
directions: In a medium saucepan cook the bacon over medium heat until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Reserving the fat in the saucepan, drain the bacon on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside.

title: carole's winner circle pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and then the butter.
Add English walnuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add cinnamon and vanilla to taste.
Pecans can be mixed in or placed on top. Place marshmallows on top.

title: easy roast
directions: Pour soups over roast.
Arrange potatoes, carrots and onion pieces around roast, if so desired.
Seal all in aluminum foil. Place in oven.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325° or 4 hours at 250°.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix into large bowl and chill.

title: layered garden pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as per package directions and drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Stir together macaroni, onions and bacon bits in medium bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, cheese, sugar and garlic powder.
In 3 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer salad greens, macaroni mixture, zucchini and cauliflowerets.
On top of this, layer broccoli and tomatoes.
Pour dressing evenly over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with bacon bits just before serving.
Refrigerate only remaining salad.
Makes 10 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook butter, salt, brown sugar and 1/2 cup white corn syrup until butter is melted.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Beat well.
Pour over corn in large bowl; mix well.
Add pecans or peanuts.
Spread this on 2 cookie sheets. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes to coat popcorn.
May be frozen if any leftover.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef with seasoning package and tomato sauce.
Spread over the beans. Continue layers according to ingredients listed.
The top layer should be the grated cheese.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes in a 350° oven until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly.
Serve with hot sauce.
Garnish with taco chips.

title: strawberry-lemonade punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir well.
Add ginger ale and stir gently.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Crush cookies in blender.
Melt butter and pour over; mix well.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan; chill.
Whip cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Prepare pudding with milk; spread over cheese mixture and chill until firm.
Spread with rest of Cool Whip.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat into small silver dollar size shapes and fry until golden brown.
Even your kids will like squash prepared this way.

title: deviled ham
directions: Spread on Melba toast.

title: south american dry rub from mississippi
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container until use.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well all the ingredients into a mixing bowl and add the cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise last.
You may want to add a little margarine for emulsion and season to taste.

title: sis. cubie's famous butter rolls
directions: Mix shortening, flour and 1/2 cup milk together.
Take dough mixture as you would biscuit dough and roll out.
Separate dough to make 5 saucer size pancakes.
In each pancake, cut up 1/4 stick butter.
Sprinkle heavy with sugar and lightly sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up and place in a casserole dish.
Take remaining butter and cut up over top of your 5 rolls and pour 1 cup of milk over the top of this and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
When butter roll is done,
if it appears dry, pour 1/2 cup more milk over top and place in oven on warm for 5 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Grease/flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, water chestnuts and soup mix.
Mix well.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: butter pecan turtle bars
directions: Mix and press in ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle 1 cup pecan halves over unbaked crust.

title: krispy kraut salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling point vinegar and sugar.
Pour hot mixture over salad mixture.
Cool and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except vanilla and topping.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Let cool.
Spread topping on top.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Each square contains less than 1/2 gram of fat.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 4 pans for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Drain well.
Mix in cheese cubes and spoon onto party rye.
Heat when needed.

title: texas short ribs
directions: Place short ribs in large frying pan or Dutch oven; cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, mustard, onion, garlic and chili powder in saucepan and simmer 5 minutes, stirring to blend.
Remove each short rib from pan.
Dip in sauce to coat all sides and place on rack in broiler pan (4 to 5 inches from heat) or on grill top over charcoal.
Cook at moderate temperature, brushing with sauce and turning occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage fine and boil until very tender in salt water. Wilt onion in butter. When wilted, add cheese in hunks and allow to melt over low heat.
When cheese has melted, add mushroom soup. Over low heat, blend well.
Then add boiled cabbage and mix well. Add bread crumbs until proper consistency, about 3/4 to 1 cup. Season to taste.
Put in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add chili block and rest of the ingredients.
Cook noodles according to package and drain. Add to the mixture and simmer in large pan, covered, for about 45 minutes, stirring from time to time.
The longer it simmers, the better the taste!

title: italian stuffed artichoke heart miniatures
directions: Cut artichoke hearts in quarters.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, and garlic salt.
Mix together olive oil and lemon juice in separate bowl.
Coat artichoke heart pieces in olive oil mixture then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet and broil till lightly toasted-about 3-5 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 60-80 canapes, depending on the number of artichokes in the can.

title: sub dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add olive oil to moisten to taste.

title: cheesy potatoes(microwave)
directions: Prick potatoes in several places with fork; place 2-inches apart in circle in microwave.
Microwave on High (100%) until tender, 11 to 13 minutes.
Le stand about 15 minutes.
Cut thin slice from top of each potato; scoop out inside, leaving thin shell.
Mash potatoes until no lumps remain.
Add small amounts of milk, beating after each addition.
(Amount of milk needed to make potatoes smooth and fluffy depends on kind of potatoes.)
Add margarine, salt and pepper; beat vigorously until potatoes are light and fluffy.
Stir in cheese.
Fill potato shells with mashed potatoes.
Arrange in circle on 10-inch microwavable plate. Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) 2 minutes.
Rotate plate 1/4 turn.
Microwave until hot, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with imitation bacon and snipped chives, if desired.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add to flour and milk paste and beat at high speed until fluffy.
Frost cooled cake.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet, drain.
Put beef in a crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions, drain.
Add all ingredients to the crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 9 hours.
Serve as a main dish with crackers or brown bread and salad.

title: rozky
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended and dough does not stick to hands. Set aside in cold place for 1 hour or longer.
Roll out on floured board and cut in squares. Fill with desired filling.
Roll and turn into crescents. Brush top with milk or beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Cook onions in frypan with butter until soft.
Melt cheese in white sauce.
Add onions.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easter pie
directions: Roll out each loaf of bread to fit into oblong greased cake pan.
Layer meats, cheeses and hard-boiled egg slices.
Place other dough on top and seal well along edges.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and brush with beaten egg.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer at 300°.
Remove and let set at least one hour before cutting.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Slice water chestnuts; wrap with bacon strip.
Insert toothpick.
Bake until bacon is crisp.

title: pork jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in heavy pot; slowly brown meat and sausage and sprinkle with flour and blend in.
Add onion, pepper, celery, seasoning and 1 cup water.
Cook very slowly over low heat for about 10 minutes or until vegetables wilt.
Add remaining water and rice.
Bring to
a boil, stirring frequently to mix meat and rice.
Cook over low heat, covered, until rice is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread butter pickles
directions: Make layers of first 5 ingredients; add ice cubes.
Soak for 4 hours.
Drain.
Mix last 6 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add pickles.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: shrimp mornay
directions: Combine wine, bouillon and water; bring to a boil.
Add shrimp, peas and onions.
Return to boil, cover, simmer for 1 minute.
Drain off liquid into small pan.
Boil down to 1/2 cup. Add milk mixed with cornstarch.
Cook and stir until bubbly and thick.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in shrimp and vegetables.
Toss with spaghetti.
Arrange in 2 (10 ounce) casseroles.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, covered or uncovered, for desired thickness.
Serves 2.

title: pastor al's favorite crackers
directions: Place water in pot and bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients to water and stir thoroughly.
Let stand or sit for 10 minutes. Spoon onto sprayed Pam cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then score and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: apricot fruit dip
directions: Beat preserves and cream cheese together.
Fold whipped cream and flavorings into cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add cranberry sauce and let dissolve as much as possible.
When room temperature, add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator and let set up, then spread sour cream over top.
Then pour remaining Jell-O mixture over top of sour cream.
Put in refrigerator and let set up, then it's ready to serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and mix all ingredients together.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven in covered pan.
Remove cover and brown for 15 minutes.

title: molded pear salad
directions: Drain pears; use juice plus necessary water to prepare Jell-O (to equal 2 cups).
Boil liquid; add Jell-O and cream cheese. Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Beat.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Add pears.
Pour into greased mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unmold onto cold plate or cut into squares if 9 x 13-inch pan is used.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: tastee sandwiches
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and Accent until brown.
Drain.
Mix seasonings together to fill 8 ounce cup.
Add to meat mixture. Cook over medium heat.
Stir often.
Don't overcook.

title: bowtie noodles
directions: In a large frying pan, saute garlic in oil.
Parboil all veggies.
Cook noodles.
Cook shrimp (boil).
Add noodles, veggies and shrimp into frying pan along with chicken broth.
Cook on medium until hot and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: woof snack mix
directions: This makes a large batch.
Keep in a covered container.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine poppy seed and buttermilk; soak overnight in refrigerator.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vanilla to buttermilk mixture. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla together. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours or more.
Top with fresh fruit or canned pie filling.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to boil sugar, coffee, cocoa and margarine; boil four minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow creme.
Beat by hand for 5 minutes.
Add chopped nuts, mix well.
Pour onto buttered dish and cut when cool.

title: scalloped mushrooms
directions: Make a cream sauce by adding 2 tablespoons flour to the melted butter.
Add cream and sour cream.
Blend with mushrooms, cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, seasonings and onion.

title: cherry or blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix crackers, 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix Dream Whip with milk and whip.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar and whip again.

title: frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour on stove; boil 1 minute.
Let thickening cool.
Mix with mixer, then add sugar, shortening, butter and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy (about 5 minutes).

title: italian meat balls with hot italian sausage
directions: Mix all together.
Make 1-inch meatballs and cook.
Cut sausage (hot Italian) into bite size pieces.
Combine with cooked meat balls.
Cover with tomato sauce; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini and onions; add salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add the flour, oatmeal, salt and soda.
Stir until crumbly.
Put 1/2 the crumble mixture in a 13 x 9 pan, then pour the pie filling.
Then cover with the rest of the crumble mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: microwave chicken breast with mushroom sauce
directions: In glass baking dish, microwave 2 tablespoons margarine, mushrooms and green onion for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Add milk, cream cheese, chicken soup base, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and cook 1 minute longer; set aside.

title: the ultimate strawberry pie
directions: Combine pie crust mix and almonds; mix in water as directed on package.
Roll out pastry on floured surface and use to line a 9 inch pie plate; crimp edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry shell with fork.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown; set aside to cool.

title: ginger's breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with margarine.
Place buttered side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Fry sausage, drain and crumble. Sprinkle sausage over bread, then add egg and milk mixture. Top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, better if it sits overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Good for breakfast or brunch.

title: um good cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Sprinkle bottom of dish with coconut.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Cream together remaining ingredients.
Add a few drops of water, if needed, for pouring consistency.
Dribble over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mehallabiyeh (pudding)
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in one cup milk.
In two-quart saucepan, combine the remaining milk and sugar and bring to boil over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat, add starch, milk mixture, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat, add starch, milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Simmer 10 minutes or until mixture is thick enough to coat spoon.
Pour in rosewater, stir and pour into large platter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: hamburger skillet dish
directions: Brown rice slowly in hot fat in a heavy skillet, stirring frequently.
Add ground beef, onion and celery.
Brown well.
Add tomatoes and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit filled cheese cakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice. Spoon into sponge cake cups. Cover with fruit and serve.

title: bakerstyle cheesecake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs (well beaten) gradually, then cottage cheese, vanilla, cornstarch and cream.
Beat thoroughly.
Add cherries.
Pour into crust lined pie tin; bake 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone chicken and strain broth.
Saute onions, celery and carrots.
Add to broth.
Simmer until tender.
Boil egg noodles.
Add chicken and noodles to vegetables.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and chicken bouillon.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix the Ranch mix and dill weed in a large bowl.
Pour in oil and mix well.
Put in crackers and stir well.
Ready to eat.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Clean and check leaves of lettuce.
Rinse and drain.
Cut bacon fine and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon.
In same frypan, add vinegar and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and bits are removed from bottom of pan.
Combine in a bowl the lettuce, sliced onion and bacon bits.
Pour over the warm vinegar solution and serve immediately.

title: easy chicken nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and coat with mayonnaise. Grind crackers into fine crumbs and place in a large Baggie. Add coated chicken and shake until all pieces are well coated. Put chicken into baking dish and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour. Serves 4.

title: lemon yoghurt ice cream
directions: Beat yoghurt and sugar together until sugar has dissolved. Add lemon rind and juice.
Taste for tartness and adjust to taste (freezing dulls sweetness).
Cover bowl and freeze 2 to 3 hours. Remove when softly frozen and beat until smooth.
Pour into mould. Replace in freezer overnight.
Decorate with slices of lemon. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Partially cook beans in boiling water; drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese, onion and beans.
Place in a lightly greased 8-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Return to oven; bake for an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and sour cream.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 325° in a greased and floured tube pan for about 1 hour.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into walnut-size balls and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together and make a paste of first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and set aside.
Mix together until crumbly (like cornmeal) of last 2 ingredients.
Next add paste mixture.
Blend well. Enough for 4 single crust pies or 2 double crust pies.

title: meatsapie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
the pizza sauce and the Mozzarella
cheese, together thoroughly.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Drain off any excess fat. Pour
the
pizza
sauce over the meat mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded
Mozzarella cheese.
Return to 325° oven for 10 minutes. Cut in squares and serve.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Toss hot spaghetti and olive oil.
Beat eggs and Parmesan cheese together and toss into spaghetti.
Pour into a lightly greased pie dish to form "crust."

title: baked ham & noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion & pepper until soft.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and mushroom soup.
In greased casserole dish, layer half the noodles, half the sauce, half the ham and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350 degrees until heated through, about 30 minutes.
If you're in a hurry, it can be heated in the microwave.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to box directions.
Saute chicken, onion and mushrooms until done.
Mix all ingredients together. Top with additional cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: irish potato bake
directions: Butter 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Thoroughly combine Corn Chex crumbs and butter; set aside.
Combine potatoes, sour cream, seasonings and broccoli.
Stir gently until well mixed. Turn 1/2 of mixture into baking dish; sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese, then with 1/2 of crumbs; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crumbs are golden.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar to look like whipped cream.
Add one egg at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings. Bake in one cake tin at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or 2 small loaf pans for approximately 1 hour.
Don't overcook.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and molasses; beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, ginger and salt; mix well.
Add flour, about a cup at a time, beating just until blended after each addition (do not overbeat).
Divide dough into ten portions and place each on a greased cookie sheet or 10-inch cake pan; pat into a 10-inch circle.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Stack the layers, spreading about 2/3 cup apple butter between each.

title: twinkie torte
directions: Melt chips in microwave.
Add water and egg yolks; cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold together the egg whites and whipped topping into chocolate mixture.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies, cut horizontally.
Spread mixture on top.
If desired, add more whipped topping and chopped nuts on top or leave plain.

title: southwestern seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
Use as a seasoning for cooked vegetables, grilled meats or chip dips. For use as dip, combine 1 tablespoon of mix with 1 cup sour cream and salt to taste.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, oleo and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Beat cream cheese into a large mixing bowl until fluffy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Pour cream cheese mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until cheesecake is set.

title: seafood spread
directions: Combine all ingredients (except seafood sauce) and mix by hand.
Shape into mound on serving dish.
Serve with crackers. Seafood sauce may be poured on top, if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Fold in apples and nuts.
Mixture will be very thick and you may have to mix with your hands.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan or rectangular baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: grilled pork loin
directions: Cut pork long 1 1/2 to 2-inches thick. Mix onion soup with 2 cups of water. Add one chicken bouillon cube. Marinate pork loins in onion soup mixture overnight.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up fryer; cover with water and boil until tender.
Remove chicken from bone.
Retain juice.
Put chicken, cream of chicken soup and seasonings in the juice.
Make dumplings of self-rising flour, milk and Crisco.
Roll on floured board.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Boil in the chicken mix until tender.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix
together
and
press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well. Add the eggs and milk and mix well. Place in a glass bowl. Cook in microwave for approximately 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Make sure mixture is thick enough, almost where a spoon will stand up in it. Add mixture to baked pie crust. Beat 2 egg whites until stiff. Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixed. Place on top of pie and brown in the oven.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Combine sugars and corn syrup in a saucepan.
Heat just to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Stir until butter melts. Gradually	stir
a
little hot mixture into eggs.	Add warmed eggs
to
mixture.	Stir
in
black walnuts.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Sprinkle over bottom of pie	crust. Pour
walnut mixture into the pastry.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: strawberry-nut salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Day Before:
Combine jello with boiling water, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.

title: broccoli pasta bake
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Microwave (High) broccoli for 7 to 8 minutes; drain and set aside.
Combine cooked macaroni and cottage cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and microwave (High) 3 to 4 minutes; stir once.
Spread evenly in casserole dish.
Top with broccoli, then spaghetti sauce.
Cover and microwave (High) 4 to 5 minutes; turn dish once.
Top with cheese and microwave 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 5.
Contains 237 calories, 6 grams fat and 9 mg. cholesterol.

title: corn crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 3 cookie sheets with vegetable spray.
Mix cornmeal and salt in bowl and pour in boiling water slowly, stirring to keep lumps from forming.
Stir in margarine.

title: spice-molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg and molasses; mix well. Combine flour and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add about one-fourth of flour mixture at a time to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition. Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 or 10 minutes.

title: open-faced cherry pie
directions: Combine cherries, tapioca, salt, Sucaryl, cherry juice and almond extract; let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour filling into crust and cover top with foil to prevent drying out.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: poi
directions: Poi should be fresh, 1 or 2 days old.
Freeze-dried or bottled poi may be substituted, although the flavor is more bland.
Squeeze poi from bag into bowl, gradually adding water.
Mix with hands until smooth, the consistency of thick paste.
Store, covered, in a cool place.
Serve at room temperature.
If poi is kept at room temperature for several days, it will sour gradually.
If refrigerated, it will sour more slowly, but should be covered with a layer of water.
It may be mixed with more water when ready to serve, as it hardens with cold.
It will serve about 20, depending on how much they like it.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Set temperature control on electric skillet at 300°.
Melt butter; add salt, pepper, onion and rice.
Stir frequently until rice is golden brown.
Add mushrooms, hot stock, parsley, thyme, lemon juice and shrimp; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes until rice is tender.

title: oven barbecued swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with mixture. Brown slowly on both sides in cooking oil.
Drain.
Place in baking dish or Dutch oven.
Combine tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Pour over steak.
Add onion slices.
Bake, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until meat is tender.

title: hollandaise trout
directions: Melt butter and mix with lemon juice and onion powder.
Arrange fish in Pyrex baking dish.
Pour butter mixture over fish.
Salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate for one hour.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer. While baking, prepare hollandaise sauce according to package directions.
Warm 3 - 5 asparagus spears for each fillet (according to size of fillet).
Place fish on plate, lay asparagus on top of fish and drizzle with hollandaise sauce.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° In tube pan.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into 4 sections.
Arrange in a jellyroll pan with edges touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to boil; cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool on wax paper.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: nut bread
directions: Set aside milk mixed with
vinegar.
Add baking soda.
Beat the eggs well.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk mixture and blend.
When mixed well, add Grape-Nuts.
Mix and pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Bread will rise in the center and burst open.
Pierce center with a long toothpick.
If it comes out clean, the bread is done.
Remove from the pans after 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar and beat.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour.
Mix all ingredients.
Line pan with waxed paper, greased well.
Bake done, but light.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with crushed pineapple.
Stir in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix in a 9 x 13-inch bowl.
Top with chopped nuts and chopped cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: scrambled potatoes
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add water, salt and Tabasco.
Set aside. Chop onion and garlic; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet; add cubed potatoes.
Saute in butter until soft and very lightly brown on edges over medium heat; do not let butter burn.
Add onion and garlic and let wilt slightly.
Pour eggs over and scramble. Serves 2 to 3.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good with Triscuits, taco flavored chips or onion crackers.

title: roasted possum ozark method
directions: First catch your possum alive.
Fatten it with mashed persimmons and warm water for a week, then kill it as you would a piglet.

Stuff with a mixture of equal parts of persimmons, sweet potatoes and bread crumbs, seasoned with savory spices (sage, thyme, parsley, rosemary, celery leaves and allspice), moistened with beef stock.
Sew up the opening.
Make two or three gashes three inches long on each side of the backbone, then place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and brush over with melted butter.
Pour two cups of boiling water around the possum and cover with buttered paper.

Now sear the possum for 15 to 20 minutes in a very hot oven (475° to 500°), then reduce the heat to slow (300°) and cook until the meat is tender (about 25 minutes to the pound), basting frequently with the liquid in the pan.
Remove the paper after cooking 2 to 2 1/2 hours and brush with heavy cream.
Then, continue roasting until delicately browned.
Serve on a large sizzling hot platter, garnished with sweet potatoes and stewed persimmons.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bake your cake mixes in the same Bundt pan, so the shape will be uniform.
When they are cool, place them, flat bottom to flat bottom.
This means one will be upside down.
Frost the whole thing orange.
Place the ice cream cone upside-down in the hole of the cake.
Frost it light green to look like the steam.
You may want to use some green to make a leaf and vine effect.
This makes a lot of cake, but it's good for Thanksgiving.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and butter together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add mashed fig preserves and water and mix well.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together and add to mixture.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until mixed and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: great macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Fry onion in margarine.
Fry bacon. Stir in soup, milk and 3/4 of the cheese.
Heat slowly while gently stirring.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Turn into small casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Gradually add mayonnaise to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in relish and mustard.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Spoon into lightly oiled 9-inch spring-form pan with ring inserted.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold and garnish with cucumber slices and radishes, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: special jellied salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and evaporated milk.
Add horseradish and salad dressing to mixture.
Refrigerate jello until partially set. Fold into the first mixture.
Chop cherries and nuts; add to mixture.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce lined plate.
Serves about 10.

title: zucchini pie(1 pie)
directions: Put all in blender until smooth.
Pour in 8-inch pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 300° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook all ingredients together for 25 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix and pineapple with juice together.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.

title: chocolate pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Beat egg yolks. Gradually add sugar, milk, flour and cocoa. Cook in a double boiler until it thickens. Add flavoring and butter. Put in a baked pie shell and add meringue.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in long or round slices and fill jars 1/2 full.
Add dill and a button of garlic.
Fill jars with more cucumbers and add a little more dill on top.

title: suzette gahagen's apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl combine thinly sliced apples, 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Layer the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with the mixture.

title: smoked beef brisket
directions: Marinate 12 hours.
Bake for 6 hours at 300°.
Cool; remove from oven.
Remove fat and slice.
Leave in broth.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, onion, celery, bacon, raisins and sunflower seeds.
About 1 1/2 hours prior to serving, add the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet good.
Place graham crackers on sheet.
In saucepan, mix brown sugar and oleo and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add pecans and boil good.
Pour over crackers and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and set aside.
Scald milk or water.
Cool till lukewarm.
Add shortening and salt.

title: cranberry-glazed pork roast
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together all ingredients except pork.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until thickened; set aside.
Place roast in shallow baking dish.
Roast at 325° for 45 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup glaze over roast and continue roasting for 30 to 45 minutes more, until internal temperature reaches 155° to 160°.
Let stand for 10 minutes and then serve with remaining sauce.
Save some of the glaze and serve hot at the table.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine reserved liquid, sugar, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in beets and margarine.
Heat through.

title: honey pork chops
directions: Slowly heat large, heavy skillet.
Wipe chops with damp paper towels.
In hot skillet, brown chops well, about 10 minutes each side.
Remove to a 3-quart casserole dish.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, about one hour or until chops are tender.
Serve with sauce spooned over.
Makes 6 servings.

title: overnight cornbread stuffing casserole
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable baking dish (or a comparably sized round dish), stir together the stuffing mix, vegetables and ham.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cornbread mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least 5 hours.
Remove plastic; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Full power, High, for 6 minutes; rotate 1/4 turn; microwave on Medium-high (80 percent power) until a knife inserted an inch from center comes out clean, 7 to 9 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir gently before serving. Yield: 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Simmer meat in water to cover until very tender and add vegetables and seasonings to meat stock.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours, stirring frequently.
If more liquid is needed, dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and add to stew.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put meat in dish.
Sprinkle with onion.
Pour chicken soup over all.
Layer with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tangy tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix remaining ingredients and chill until stiff.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract until smooth.
Pour into greased spring-form pan or 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Mix and put in muffin pans and bake at 400° until done.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix dressing, mustard, garlic powder and chicken base with a little pickle or olive juice.
Set aside.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in large bowl and mix with dressing.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In deep baking dish, pour rice (uncooked), then add bouillon cubes and boiling water.
Crush cubes with fork and stir mixture.
Lay chicken breasts on rice; cover chicken pieces with soup.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until rice is done. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger. Put in crock-pot. Add tomato paste. Stir well. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Cook 4 hours on high.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large salad bowl mix cooked pasta and defrosted vegetables. Mix in olives.
Toss with Caesar salad dressing.

title: country casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and vegetables; drain grease.
Add tomato sauce to meat mixture.
Put half of the meat mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer half the cheese and layer the rest of the meat mixture and cheese.
Spoon the prepared mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies or tea cakes
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; mix in eggs.
Add sour milk.
Stir in the extracts.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time to mix it well. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Roll out dough. Use press cookie cutters.

title: blueberry special
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and line bottom of pan with half of the mixture.
Cook until thick the blueberries, sugar and cornstarch mixed with small amount of water.
Whip cream and fold marshmallows into cream.
Add alternate layers of mixtures: crumbs, blueberries, cream, ending with crumbs.
Chill.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add margarine (melted), vanilla and milk.
Ice cake.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Refrigerate and allow to set.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed and cool.
Add other ingredients to the reserved artichoke liquid and add 1/4 teaspoon curry and 1/3 cup mayonnaise.
Mix together and then toss together with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press raw ground beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spread both cans of soup on top of onion soup mix.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion with oleo.
Mix with green beans and water chestnuts.
Put half this mixture in casserole dish and top with 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Add other half of mixture and top with 1/2 can mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Add onion rings and brown lightly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add flour and sugar; stir to blend.
Add milk and vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture thickens and boils, remove from heat and add oleo.
Stir until melted.
Add sliced bananas.
Layer with vanilla wafers in bowl.

title: sand cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7-ounce) plastic cups.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Drain liquid from green beans.
Add dressing and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Drain and serve cold.
Serve with chicken salad or chicken breast for a light lunch or that special dinner.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain liquid off all fruit. Combine fruit, Cool Whip and pistachio pudding.
Use a large bowl.
Stir and mix completely. Chill and serve.

title: seven layer rainbow jello
directions: Grease lightly with salad oil a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex glass pan. Dissolve lime Jell-O using 1 1/2 cups boiling water and pour into pan. Refrigerate to set.

title: chocolate cherry ring
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in pie filling, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: leftover chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add broccoli and then a layer of chicken.
Mix the cream of chicken soup, curry, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with grated cheese and top with croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place washed and cut berries in bottom of pie shells.
Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch.
Heat until clear and thick. Add Jell-O.
Pour over berries.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Divide Rich Sweet Dough in half.
Roll each half into 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
Brush slightly with melted margarine.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2/3 cup raisins.
Sprinkle each oblong with half of mixture.
Roll up from 9 inch side like a jelly roll.
Cut each roll into 9 equal pieces.
Place, cut side up, about 1 inch apart in 2 greased 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cover with clean towel and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.

title: incredible pecan tart
directions: Put in processor the flour.
Combine powdered sugar and butter. Press into spring-form or foil-lined pan, 3/4-inch up the sides.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into 6 patties.
Pan-fry, browning on each side well.
Serve warm.

title: leah's marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Good on chicken or steak.

title: layer cake surprise
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together for first layer.
Spread over with chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs together and most of 10x sugar.
Spread on top of second layer. Sprinkle some sugar on top when done.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute peppers, onions,	celery	and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir
in remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Add
shrimp
to sauce and simmer ten minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a double boiler over boiling water, melt chips with milk. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in well-buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours; cut in squares. Yield:
2 pounds.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese lasagna
directions: Steam or boil broccoli until tender; drain.
Cook lasagna as directed on box.
Drain; let sit in cool water (this helps it not to stick together).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, add 1/2 cup of water.
Put a layer of pasta on bottom of pan.
Mix together the cottage cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and spices in a large mixing bowl.
Spread some of this cheese mixture over lasagna and then lay broccoli over that.
Continue to layer pasta, cheese mixture and broccoli, until completed.
Top with leftover Mozzarella cheese; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 35.

title: delicious lemon cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 2 layers. Cool, then slice each layer through, making 4 layers. Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemonade concentrate and Cool Whip. Ice layers. Keep refrigerated.

title: ham pate
directions: Brown onion very slowly in butter.
Stir often.
Wash mushrooms; slice and chop into small pieces, stems and all.
Add these to the onion after about 1/2 hour.
Keep on cooking for another 1/2 hour, adding more butter.
When all the water from mushrooms has evaporated, crumble chicken bouillon cubes over mushroom and onion mixture.
Pour in the mushroom soup.
Stir and scrape to get all the good brown residue from the bottom of pan and to spread the bouillon cubes throughout.
Transfer to a chafing dish and pass crackers or Melba toast.
Let guests spread their own.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place each chicken breast half between two pieces of plastic wrap.
Working from center, lightly pound with flat side of meat mallet to 1/8-inch thickness.
Remove plastic wrap.
In flat dish, combine the flour, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Lightly press the chicken pieces into flour mixture, coating both sides and shaking off any excess flour mixture.
Lightly spray an unheated large skillet with nonstick spray.
Add the mushrooms and chives.
Cook and stir until tender.
Remove the mushroom mixture from the skillet.
Add the chicken to the skillet and cook over medium-high heat for 4 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Return the mushroom mixture to the skillet.
Carefully, add the broth and Marsala. Cook uncovered for 2 to 3 minutes or until the mushroom mixture slightly thickens, stirring occasionally.
Transfer the chicken to a serving platter.
Spoon the mushroom mixture over the chicken. Makes 4 servings.

title: "3" bean salad
directions: Mix in a jar and pour over beans the vinegar, salt, sugar, pepper and oil.

title: chicken in sake
directions: Cut chicken into
small pieces and sprinkle with garlic salt. Dip in egg	mixture
and
coat
with
flour.
Deep fry. Combine sake, shoyu and sugar and cook together until sugar is dissolved. Place chicken in a shallow pan and brush on glaze. Bake in the oven for about 5 minutes at 350°.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, sugar, onions and peppers; let stand 1 hour after mixed.
Bring to a boil vinegar, Wesson oil, celery seed and sugar.
Pour over cabbage and refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: go go shake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend in blender until smooth.
Serves 2.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Boil together the margarine and brown sugar for 1 minute; let cool.
Add milk.
Beat smoothly, then add the xxxx sugar.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over hot water.
Measure sugar Frosted Flakes and crush.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Fold in crushed sugar Frosted Flakes. Swirl warm melted chocolate lightly through batter, leaving streaks of chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: carrot cucumber relish
directions: Combine ground vegetables; stir in salt.
