Let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Combine the rest of ingredients and bring to boil.
Add vegetables; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Seal in jars. Chill before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: ham and cheese strada
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes clean.

title: tuna pockets
directions: Mix together first seven ingredients.
Cut pita breads in half.
Fill with tuna. Yields 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 2 cups Cool Whip, peanut butter and sugar.
Place half of the Hershey bar shavings on the bottom of the pie crust.
Pour pie filling into crust.
Top with Cool Whip and remainder of Hershey bar shavings.
Let cool in refrigerator before serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add all ingredients and shrimp.
Whip up.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread pecans and coconut into pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Spoon over cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and pineapple juice together.
Sweeten by putting sugar in, then pour in one gallon jug.
Fill rest of jug with water.
Stir in Jell-O.
Put in freezer and freeze until slushy consistency.
Stir or shake often.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and beat until stiff.
Slowly add 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 2/3 cup nuts.
Fold in 14 crackers.
Put in well-greased 9-inch pie pan and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 2 hours.
Cover pie with whipped cream; sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Chill 1 hour.

title: huevos enchiladas
directions: Saute mushrooms, bell pepper, and 1/2 of onions along with diced ham and 1/4 stick butter in a large skillet.
Add remaining butter and well beaten eggs.
Scramble.
Salt and pepper to taste.
While cooking, add 1 cup grated cheese.
When cooked, roll the scrambled eggs in tortillas to make nice plump enchiladas.

title: elegant chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, softened margarine and nuts together and press in the bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix together for two minutes or until thick; the instant pudding with the milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Top with layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with crushed nuts. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: kabob sauce
directions: Mix and bring to boil.
Put meat in and soak overnight and then grill, or just use as barbecue sauce.
Will tenderize tougher meats.

title: beef and beans
directions: Add meat to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Melt butter.
Combine crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano and garlic salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then crumb mixture. Place in ungreased pan and bake 50-60 minutes.
Add green onion and parsley to rest of butter and pour over chicken.
Bake 3-5 minutes longer.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but potato chips in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Stir and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle on chips and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: pastichio with crema sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until slightly brown.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread Crema evenly over macaroni.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cream sauce should be thick enough to form a top layer. Thin sauce will seep through macaroni.
Makes 12 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Brown pork sausage.
Mix macaroni, cooked, drained sausage and soup together. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top and bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well before adding milk.
Add milk; mix well. Put into a 4-quart freezer and prepare.

title: pita bread salad(fatoosh)
directions: Chop, slice or tear preceding ingredients; toss together.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix sugars, spiced and flour. Add vinegar. Mix, then add to green tomatoes. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then let stand at least 1/2 hour to set.

title: meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Add boiling water.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Add sugar gradually.
Add cornstarch mixture all at once. Beat until blended.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: new orleans style beignets(ben-yae)
directions: In a large mixer bowl, stir together 1 1/4 cups of the flour, yeast and nutmeg, if desired.

In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, 2 tablespoons shortening and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) and the shortening is almost melted, stirring the mixture constantly. Add the heated mixture to the flour mixture.
Add egg.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed.
Using a spoon, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: pasta (penne) with ricotta and spinach sauce(appetizer or light main dish)
directions: Cook fresh spinach until tender (for frozen spinach, just thaw).
Chop fine and drain water.
Melt butter in a skillet or saute pan.
Add spinach and a liberal 2 or 3 pinches of salt. Saute for 2 minutes or so.
Cook the pasta.
To the spinach add the Ricotta cheese and the Parmesan cheese.
Mix the pasta with the spinach/cheese sauce.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange squares
directions: Chill milk until icy.
Dissolve gelatins in 1 cup boiling water; chill until thickened.
Whip milk until stiff, adding sugar and orange juice.
Add gelatin; beat until light and fluffy. Spread cracker crumbs in waxed paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pour in filling.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Add beef. Cook and stir until browned. Add 1 1/2 cups water, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaves, garlic, paprika and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cover. Simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove and discard bay leaves. Add carrots, potatoes and onions. Cover. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender. Add beans. Simmer 5 minutes or until tender. Remove from heat. Add 1 cup water to Dutch oven. Combine remaining 1/4 cup water and cornstarch in small bowl. Stir well. Stir into ingredients in Dutch oven. Return to low heat. Cook and stir until thickened. Season with salt, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with flour.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add lemon rind and juice, then milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to mixture.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 425° approximately 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until top is medium brown.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt oleo
and	while
still
hot,
stir
in
flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: famous caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a skillet.
When dark brown and melted, add water.
When sugar is dissolved, remove from heat. Mix flour. cornstarch, milk, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir into this mixture the caramelized sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add gelatin dissolved in cold water.
Cool and fill shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except for paprika, together.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover for first 15 or 20 minutes.

title: kurtz's hot buttered rum
directions: Mix spices with sugar.
Cream in butter.
Store in refrigerator, covered.
For a 4 ounce serving, use 1 heaping teaspoon of mix and 1 shot of rum.
Fill with hot water.
Stir and garnish with a cinnamon stick.

title: winter fruit delight
directions: Peel and section grapefruit, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 1 cup. Combine juice, sugar and marmalade in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add cranberries and boil 5 to 8 minutes or until skins pop.
Cool; stir in grapefruit.
Cover and chill.
Slice bananas and stir in chilled mixture just before serving. This mixture will keep in the refrigerator up to a week.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 4 teaspoons lukewarm water.
In a large bowl, place Crisco.
Pour boiling water over Crisco.
Let cool, then add sugar, beaten eggs, salt and yeast.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add about 4 cups flour or enough to make a stiff dough.
Let rise. Use muffin pans to make rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and catsup in small bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in shrimp on low speed. Remove from refrigerator for 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 cups dip.

title: apple-pear salad
directions: Mix apples, pears and celery.
Shake lemon juice, honey, salt and pumpkin pie spice in a tightly covered container.
Toss with apple mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Arrange on lettuce leaves. Yields 8 servings.
Has 55 calories per serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate overnight in 2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup white vinegar.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill a large pot with water and bring to a soft boil.

Add the following ingredients in the order listed below. Add entire can of seasoning, corn, sausage, and onions and allow to cook for about five minutes. Add shrimp and cook until the shrimp are good and pink.
Allow low country boil to sit in water for about thirty minutes.
This will allow the items to absorb the flavor. Drain the water and serve with your favorite cocktail sauce.

title: carrot-raisin-pineapple  relish
directions: Mix carrots, raisins and drained pineapple in a bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Toss lightly to mix.
Chill at least 30 minutes. Combine mayonnaise, cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Stir into carrot mixture just before serving.
Serve as a side dish or in lettuce cups as a salad.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cut sausage, drained, on top.
Top this with shredded cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until foamy.
Add zucchini and vanilla; sift in dry ingredients.
While beating well, add nuts. Divide batter into 3 pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in oven at 325°.
Let set 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chips to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal that is in a very large mixing bowl. Toss quickly until coated.
Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time.
Press into pan.
Let stand 1 hour.
Makes 48 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: raspberry fruit soup
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, salt, water and 1 package raspberries in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: bettys' apple crisp pudding
directions: Cream together margarine and Brown sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Salt chicken to taste.
Stew in about 2 cups water until tender.
Let cool.
Dice chicken into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle butter over chicken.
Add pepper to taste.
Add layer of drained Veg-All.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and milk; pour over chicken and Veg-All.
Heat to boiling the soup and chicken broth.
Top with this and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Butter casserole and cover bottom with stuffing.
Spread mixture on top of stuffing. Then add rest of stuffing.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with raw bacon slices and stuffed olive slices before baking.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish at 325° for one hour.

title: greek meat sauce for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil.
Add salt and pepper, paprika, chili powder, tomato paste and water.
Simmer until meat is well cooked.
Add hot pepper if desired.
The hotter, the better.
Cook hot dogs.
Add mustard or catsup.
Put shredded onion on dog and top with 2 to 3 teaspoons of sauce.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk together and cook over high heat until it boils.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes (no more) and remove from heat.
Add oats and peanut butter and mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: chocolate date cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of a 9-inch square pan.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add water and flour. Add nuts and shape into small fingers. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° or 350° until brown, about 10 minutes.

title: lazy man's lasagne
directions: Brown meat and set aside.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream. Set aside.
Prepare an 11 x 14-inch pan and layer pizza sauce, lasagne noodle strips, browned meat, cottage cheese and sour cream mixture, Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup water.
Repeat layering as above.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake 15 additional minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to sit for approximately 20 minutes.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Heat cheese soup and mix with Ragu.
Brown hamburger.
Put all together and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon
and cloves; sift together.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, raisins and nuts.
Add flour alternately with hot applesauce.
Beat after each addition.
Pour into a greased loaf pan (7 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sponge cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder and stir into mixture.
Gently place in 8 or 9-inch greased and floured tin and bake for 30 minutes at 360°.
Split along centre when cool and sandwich with jam and whipped cream.

title: fantasy fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and milk; cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from burner and add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until glossy.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan, well-greased.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix the flour, butter and nuts together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop first four ingredients by hand or in food processor. Combine with soup and mayonnaise.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven. Mix crackers, cheese and margarine and spread over casserole. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Debone, skin and cut chicken breasts in chunks.
Seed and chunk peppers and quarter tomatoes.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Place apples in buttered pie plate.
Work together sugar, flour cinnamon and softened butter until crumbly and put on apples.
Add a little water and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve with a little whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: pineapple bacon wraps
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and chopped onion.
Stir in rice.
Pour this on top of cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour over meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Add more water, if necessary.
Serve hot.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Fold in crabmeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a rectangular pan.

title: orange pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in orange juice completely.
Chill thoroughly.
Then fold in whipped cream.

title: tomato pie
directions: In pie crust, layer bell pepper, onion, tomato, cheese and sausage.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with another crust. Hamburger meat may also be used.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream the butter in a bowl. Add sugar and egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas. Add nuts and beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes for a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or 1 hour for 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan or 50 to 60 minutes for 4 mini loaves.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add margarine and cut in, adding a little water, if stiff.
Shape into balls; let set 5 minutes.
Cook in chicken or beef broth.

title: venison loin marinade
directions: Slice loin in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in a large bowl.
Salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Mix marinade separately.
Stir together teriyaki sauce, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Pour over venison and marinate 24 hours.
Cook on grill 2 to 3 minutes on each side (medium-rare) or lightly fry 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with rice and collards.

title: school rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together.
Roll and cut.
Let rise until doubled.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Butter tops. Yield: 150 (1 1/2 ounce) rolls.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into two buttered pie plates.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange glaze
directions: Mix ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over hot cake. Leave in pan overnight.
Remove cake from pan and store.
Cake will remain good for weeks.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix in sugar and oleo.
Mix in water and oat mixture.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add 1/2 package chips in dough.
Pour in pan and sprinkle the rest of the chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's milk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.
Mom made this when she had extra pie dough.
It's like a heavy custard pie.

title: sunkist lemon icebox pie
directions: Pour milk into ice cube tray and chill until crystals start to form.
Separate eggs.
Mix yolks with sugar, juice and peel.
Beat egg whites stiff, then lightly mix in yolk mixture.
Turn chilled milk into bowl.
Beat stiff; carefully fold into egg mixture.
Pour into ice cube tray lined with Spiced Crumbs.
Decorate top with lemon peel twist and freeze.

title: italian baked frittata
directions: In 10-inch nonstick ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir broccoli, mushrooms, red pepper and green onions in margarine until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat Egg Beaters, cottage cheese, mustard and Italian seasoning until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into skillet over vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat together and pour in uncooked pie crust.
Cook in 325° to 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in blender.
While blending, slowly add shrimp and blend.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies*
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine until soft.
Add sugars gradually and blend until creamy.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Add 1 cup of sifted flour.
Add more as needed.
Dough should be soft but not sticky.
Roll dough in balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press in crisscross pattern with a fork.
Dip fork in water before pressing to prevent sticking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato stew
directions: Cook potatoes.
Brown meat and onions; drain.
Combine meat, potatoes and soup and at least 1 soup can of potato water.
Add more potato water, if needed.

title: melon bubbles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1/4 cup.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Measure 1 1/3 cups Jell-O into a small bowl; add melon.
Pour into individual dessert glasses.
Whip remaining Jell-O at high speed with electric mixer until fluffy, thick and about doubled in volume.
Spoon over Jell-O in glasses.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with additional melon balls.
Makes 6 to 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: golden cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges with juice according to package directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together pudding, pineapple and milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix 1/2 cup mayonnaise with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Toss with ingredients.
Let set overnight.
The longer it sets the better it gets.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine egg yolks and milk.
Mix well. Add sugar, flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add oleo, vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Pour into baked crust. Spread meringue over filling, sealing edges to crust.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup coconut.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and parsley. Shape into ball and chill. Roll into chopped pecans and parsley.

title: tender pot roast
directions: Put the meat in baking dish and pour tomato juice over it. Pierce the meat several times and let stand overnight.
The next day put the roast in cooking bag and squeeze lemon juice over it. Season with 1 tsp. salt.
Cook for 3 1/2 - 4 hours in the tomato juice until tender.
After it has cooked, add the vegetables. Thicken juice for gravy if desired.

title: cheese and fruit kabobs
directions: Arrange cheese and fruit on skewers.

title: creole meatballs and noodles
directions: Combine meat, stuffing, applesauce, salt and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 16 balls (about 1/4 cup each). Saute in hot oil in large skillet and push browned meat to one side.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are softened.
Add tomato paste, watter and oregano.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve meat and sauce over hot noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook the first six ingredients in Dutch oven or large kettle until potatoes are almost done.
Add broccoli and cauliflower (fresh may be used).
Cook until cauliflower is done.
Reduce heat and add soup, water chestnuts and Velveeta cheese.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix tapioca, 3 tablespoons of sugar, salt, egg yolk and milk in saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Beat egg whites in small bowl with electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons of sugar. Beat until soft peaks form.
Add the tapioca mixture.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar.
Beat in all other ingredients.
Pour in shallow pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool, cut in squares.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain off water. Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan; add flour and cook until well blended. Add pepper, garlic powder, salt and onions. Add milk and chicken broth; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in cooked broccoli. Reduce heat and add cheese gradually over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla wafers and topping. Place a vanilla wafer at the bottom of muffin/cupcake liner.
Fill each cup 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool completely.
Top with favorite fruit topping.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks.
Beat whites until they become stiff; add cream of tartar to hold them and set aside.
Beat whipping cream until it begins to thicken, then gradually add 1 tablespoon of sugar and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until blended; gradually add the coffee or light cream; when eggs become lite lemon color, add remaining sugar, next milk, vanilla, nutmeg and rum.
Mix continually.
Carefully pour this into punch bowl and gently fold in whipped cream and egg whites.

title: black-eyed bean soup
directions: Use heavy 6-quart pot.
Put in beans and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cover and remove from heat. Allow to stand 1 hour. Return to heat. Add all other ingredients except spinach.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
May steam spinach separately and add to soup.
Could add greens last 10 minutes to cook.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring all of the ingredients to a boil over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Pour over popped corn, stirring to coat well. Spread in large pans with sides and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Turn out onto counter covered with wax paper to cool. Store in tins.

title: chicken and rice(casserole)
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together mushroom soup, French onion soup, mushrooms, rice and onion soup mix, along with 2 cans of water.
(Use the empty soup cans for measuring water.)
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top of mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Foil may be removed during the last 1/2 hour so chicken can brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with fruit kabobs or sliced fruit.

title: salsa dip 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until thick, about 2 hours, stirring often.

title: jelly bean jollies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in egg, baking soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Mix well.
Add jelly beans. Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: baby animal formula
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in covered jar and store in refrigerator.
Shake before using.
If you use whole milk, you can add a little hot water each time.
Warm before using.

title: vegi pizza squares
directions: Press dough in cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 8 minutes and mix cheese with onions and dressing.
Let stand for one hour.
Top with vegies, then top with Jack cheese.
Cut in squares.

title: homemade cavatellis
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
Add water to flour.
Mix well. Roll into thin ropes; cut into small pieces.
If freezing, put on a cookie sheet until frozen, then bag.
If cooking right away, place in boiling water with salt and oil.
Cook until they come to the top.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water, eggs and butter.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased round cake pans until done.
Cool; split layers in half with thread.

title: mexican chicken cheese ball
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except chips; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chips.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for at least 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat one minute after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Begin and end with flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix thoroughly; make into balls and press into greased muffin pans.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon bananas
directions: Make 12-inch square of heavy foil.
Peel bananas on one side, leaving rest of peel on.
Combine butter, juice and salt.
Brush on peeled side of banana.
Arrange on foil.
Grill 3 inches from coals for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Brown salted chicken pieces in butter.
Put aside.
Add rice to butter and saute until a light brown color.
Add water, onions and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve bouillon cubes.
Stir in salt.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with the browned chicken.
Cover and cook for 50 minutes at 375°.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut the top off the bunch of celery.
Cut the very bottom off too.
Pull apart the celery.
Wash the celery very well under cold water.
Fill each "log" with cream cheese.
Put a few raisins on top.
These are the "ants."
Cut up the logs and serve them on a plate.

title: grape cranberry lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, mix together grape cranberry drink, lemonade concentrate and water.
Stir.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Preheat deep fryer.
Peel onion
and separate into rings. Wash onion rings.
Prepare pancake mix, using enough water to mix batter (being careful not to make batter too thin).
Dip onion rings into batter and drop into deep fryer.
Fry until brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare lime, orange and cherry jello separately using 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water for each jello mix.
Pour into 3 separate 8 x 8-inch pans; chill until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Next, heat pineapple juice to boiling.
Remove from heat. Add 1/4 cup sugar and lemon jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Grind pecans, onion and garlic.
Mix Velveeta cheese, cream cheese, pecans, onion and garlic.
Roll into 1 big ball and roll in chili powder.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: banana lumpia
directions: Cut in half lengthwise ripe saba (cooking) bananas.
Dip each half in a mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Wrap each half in one lumpia wrapper.
Fry until crisp.
Nice to serve on bamboo barbecue sticks.

title: lemony steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steaks; slash edges to prevent curling. Pat dry with paper towel.
In large skillet, combine oil, butter, mustard, garlic and black pepper.
Heat until bubbly.
Saute steaks in the seasoned butter for 4 or 5 minutes or to desired doneness. Remove steaks and keep warm.
Add lemon and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over steaks and sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: original salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together salad dressing, water and sugar.
Add to the mixture the soda, flour, cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Mix and bake in loaf pan until done at 350°.
Ice with favorite frosting.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Grease a 9x13 pan.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Add the strawberries, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve with strawberries, white grapes and chunk pineapple.

title: colossal cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart bowl.
Put in microwave oven. Cook covered for 6 minutes, stirring once. Let stand for 2 minutes.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Brown lightly onions and celery.
Mix everything together. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet; press with fork. Bake at 325° for 18 minutes.

title: fruity muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Break egg into another bowl. Add sugar and whisk until smooth. Whisk in butter and vanilla. Stir in apple, cranberries and raisins.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Fold in until all are moistened.
Spoon batter into cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until browned and firm to touch.
Let cool.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind bologna and sweet pickles together.
Place in a large bowl and add salad dressing so mixture is moist.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Use on any kind of crackers or serve on bread.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown onion in fat and add all ingredients except chicken, simmer 30 minutes, makes 2 cups.
Have chicken cut up.
Brush chicken with sauce and place in oven 325°.
Turn chicken several times and baste with sauce.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops for about 3 minutes on each side.
Place about 2-inches of potatoes on bottom of dish.
Then place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Mix soup mix with hot water, then pour over pork chops and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, covered. Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: no-seal sweet pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and cover with boiling water. Let stand overnight, then drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers. Let stand for 5 days, adding 1 cup sugar each day.
Stir well. You do not have to seal or refrigerate.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Bring Karo syrup, sugar and butter to a boil and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Stir well and spread in a buttered pan (size of cookie sheet) and press down all around. Melt in a pan over hot water the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on top of cereal mixture.
Cut while warm.

title: corn souffle
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls flat to edge of cookie sheet for crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing (if too dry to spread add more dressing).
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Chop all vegetables (omit veggies you don't like and add what you do like).
Mix vegetables and sprinkle over cream cheese.
Top with shredded cheese and tomato.
(Low-fat cream cheese and salad dressing may be used.)

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cut angel food cake in bite-size pieces; set aside.
Cook pudding as directed on package.
When thickened, stir in 1/2 of the Angel Flake coconut.
Stir angel food cake into pudding.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Cook stuffing as directed by package.
In bowl, mix together beef, soup mix, eggs and breadcrumbs.
Form meat mixture into 4 large balls.
Place large meatballs in ungreased shallow baking dish, approximate size 8 x 8-inch.
With fingers, push down center of meatballs to form 4 separate nest shaped balls.
Evenly fill center of meatballs with stuffing.
Pour gravy over meatballs, cover pan and bake one hour at 350°.
Spoon off excess fat.
Serve with mashed potatoes and your favorite vegetable.
Serves 4.

title: buried treasure
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Using a spoon, scoop out 4 balls of frozen whipped topping and place in 4 dessert glasses.
Spoon pudding over whipped topping in glasses.
Chill. Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: cantaloupe cooler
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a blender for a sweet, foamy drink.
Makes four 4-ounce servings.

title: cocktail peppers
directions: Cut each pepper and wiener into 3 equal pieces.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and catsup together.
Add cut up peppers and wieners.
Cook over moderate heat until peppers are tender.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.
Any kind of wieners will do.

title: tabouleh
directions: Pour 2 1/2 cups boiling water over bulgar; let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.
To make dressing, stir together lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, salt and mint leaves.
Toss bulgar with dressing, tomato, parsley and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours to blend flavors.
Serve salad on a platter lined with romaine leaves.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.
Serves 8.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine corn with butter, milk, flour, salt and sugar in bowl. Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish. Place dish in baking pan half filled with boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until pudding is set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add sauce, paste and water for each can to ground meat.
Add seasoning and spices.
Simmer about 2 hours.

title: sallie knouse's sliced sweet potato pie
directions: (This is from Sallie Knouse's recipe book.)

title: southwest style sandwiches
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, onion and chili peppers.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
For each sandwich, split one corn bread square; top both halves with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts, spoon meat mixture over cheese. Top with additional cheese if desired.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together. Pour in graham cracker crust.

title: sun-dried tomato pesto butter
directions: In the bowl of a food processor, place tomatoes, Parmesan cheese and garlic; whirl until tomatoes are finely chopped.
Add butter, salt and black pepper; whirl until combined.
Pack into covered containers and refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve. Use as a spread for toasted Italian bread or on hot pasta or rice.
Can be melted and basted on chicken or fish.

title: mom's beef barbecue
directions: Add water to hamburger and simmer.
Add carrot, celery and onion; simmer until done.
Mix all other ingredients and simmer so not so juicy.

title: eagle brand milk(sweetened condensed milk)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 (14 ounce) can.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Add ingredients to crock-pot and cook 10 hours on low. Freezes well.

title: individual cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients except olives.
Pinch off one teaspoon and olive in center; shape until it's a smooth ball.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Keep watch. These can be made ahead and frozen for later use, omitting the baking part.

title: stuffing for tomatoes, peppers or cabbage
directions: Heat oil
or
shortening
and cook green onions, garlic and green
pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix carefully,	so
as	not to break shrimp.
Fill 6 tomatoes, peppers or	cabbage
leaves
and
set in baking pan.
Sprinkle tops with bread
crumbs.
Pour
tomato
sauce around them and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Spread dough on greased cookie sheet.
Lay pepperoni on dough. Sprinkle cheese over pepperoni.
Roll up like a loaf.
Seal ends and bake at 350° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Cook pineapple slowly.
Put sugar in a bowl, then sour cream, then Cool Whip.
Do not beat, just fold until sugar is gone.
Let layers and pineapple cool very good and then put together.

title: sweet strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease two (8 x 4) loaf pans. Divide batter between the 2 pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool thoroughly before slicing. Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a wooden or glass bowl with a wooden spoon. Mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured 10-inch Bundt or pound cake pan. Bake for 1 hour or until it springs back at the touch.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn onto a cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Spoon Peach Cream Cheese Frosting over top and drizzle over sides.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Combine egg and vanilla extract. Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Combine all three mixtures and add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine all together and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza balls
directions: Mix together and shape into medium-size balls (golf ball size).
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Add oil, eggs and plums.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in Bundt or tube pan.

title: feather dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, butter and enough milk to make a moist, stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling liquid.
Cover and simmer for 18 minutes.

title: grandma sophie's wine cookies
directions: Combine
oil,
sugar,
wine and 1 cup flour.
Beat with mixer. Using dough hooks add 1 to 2 cups flour or until dough is stiff. Turn out and knead, adding 1 to 2 cups flour (total 4 cups flour). Dough
should
be	smooth and elastic.
Can be mixed by hand if you
don't	have
dough
hooks.
Break
off a small amount of dough and roll on board to make a rope 12-inch to 18-inch long. Cut
in
pieces
the length and thickness of middle finger.
Loop into
a circle and join (should look like tiny doughnuts).	Dip one
side in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie
sheet, sugar side up.
Bake
at
for
to
30 minutes.
They will
be lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: fried pork chops
directions: Sprinkle rubbed sage on each chop; coat well with flour.
In large frying pan, place the Crisco.
Get Crisco hot.
Place chops in hot Crisco for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn chops over; chops will brown better in hot Crisco.
Reduce heat and cook until done.

title: meatless protein loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-oiled loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: turkey sausage
directions: Mix spices and sprinkle gradually into ground turkey, blending well.
If desired, mix 2 parts sausage to 1 part whole wheat bread crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible, to blend seasonings. Make patties and cook in nonstick skillet; use oil, if necessary.

title: quick potatoes(for grill)
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes with skins on.
Put in an aluminum pan. Slice onion on top.
Put in chunks of butter, salt and pepper. Cover with aluminum foil.
Place on back of grill while doing meat.
Leave on grill 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Serve with your meat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Run cold water over cooked macaroni to cool.
In bowl, add macaroni, cheese, peppers, olives, celery and carrots.
Pour salad dressing over ingredients and toss.
Add croutons on top after refrigerating for 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: cornflake pie crust(good for lemon, butterscotch or any pudding)
directions: Toss all ingredients and press firmly to the bottom and side of 9 or 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes and fill with pudding.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add small amount of mixture to egg yolks, then stir into remaining custard.
Cook 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix 1 cup of mixture with 3 tablespoons of peanut butter.
Spread on bottom of pie shell.
Put remaining custard on top.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 400° until meringue is browned.

title: french meat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fry in Dutch oven.
Push aside.
Mash potatoes in grease or pork until it is absorbed.
Place in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Brown chicken in Crisco.
Take up chicken (keep warm).
Put rice, onion and green peppers in pan.
Brown lightly.
Add water, tomato sauce and rest of ingredients.
Simmer 40 minutes or until rice is done.
About 10 minutes before it is done, add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and then chicken.
Cover and finish cooking.
If it gets too dry, add more water.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine other ingredients, pour over hot base, put back in oven for 20 to 25 minutes more.
Sprinkle top with xxx sugar.

title: eggless wet bottom molasses cake
directions: Crumb together flour, sugar and oil; set 1 cup aside for crumb topping.
Into remaining crumbs add 1 cup molasses and 1 teaspoon baking soda dissolved in 2 cups warm water.
Pour this into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and top with the cup of crumbs that were set aside.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Delicious and easy!

title: mexican meatballs
directions: Combine taco seasoning mix and water.
Add green chilies and ground beef.
Mix well.
Form into 1-inch meatballs.
Bake on ungreased pan in preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350°. Makes 40 meatballs.

title: soda bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in a bowl. Add raisins.
Beat eggs with buttermilk in a small bowl.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in butter.
Pour into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: annie's salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to jello mixture; chill.

title: mom's "million dollar" chicken
directions: Mix well ketchup, honey and soy sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.

title: peanut butter cup squares
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Add peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix thoroughly.
Pat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler over medium-low heat.
When melted, spread evenly over pan mixture.
Cool in refrigerator until chocolate is firm.
Before cutting, let pan get to room temperature or squares will crack into pieces.
Enjoy!

title: mother's jam cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla, milk and a cup of jam; mix well.
Add flour, spices, raisins and nuts.
Makes a large 5 layer cake.
Bake each pan about 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: honey drops
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in honey and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour and soda. Chill until firm (several hours or overnight).
Heat oven to 350°. Form dough into balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown and top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool slightly.
Put together in pairs with apricot jam between.
Makes 3 dozen double cookies.

title: ceviche(mexican seafood salad)
directions: Tear fish fillets into small pieces and place in a glass bowl. Add shrimp meat and crab meat, also torn into small pieces. Squeeze juice from lemons over fish.
It should be enough to just cover the seafood.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir once or twice during refrigeration.
Peel cucumber and chop.
Place in a bowl.
Add chopped tomato, onion, grated carrot and cilantro to taste.
Add drained olives.
Drain fish and add vegetables.
Mix well.
Serve on Tostadas with a few dashes of hot sauce and some chopped cilantro.

title: oven-baked french toast
directions: Cut bread into about 16 slices.
Arrange on jelly roll pan. In large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over bread.
Coat evenly until all is absorbed. Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Place bread on sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fried corn
directions: In a large skillet, fry the salt pork slices until crisp. Remove from skillet and measure drippings.
You will need about 1/4 cup of drippings in the skillet.
Add corn, 1 cup water, and sugar.
Add remaining water as needed.
Cook over medium heat until corn is tender and thickened.
Taste and add salt, if needed.
The amount of water needed will depend on how much starchy liquid you get from the corn.
Also, some salt pork is more salty than others, so tasting is essential to determine whether or not salt should be added before serving.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Roll out biscuits to 2-inch rounds and place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush top of each with 1 or 2 drops of salad oil.
Put 1 teaspoon sauce on each.
Top with 3 slices of pepperoni and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chops in casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large 2 1/2 quart baking dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes and onion.
Brown pork chops in skillet with small amount of fat.
Season with salt and pepper and lay on top of potato mixture.
Pour tomato soup over all. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: my mom's cheesey baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle desired amount of Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes (depending on desired consistency).

title: pinto beans(tasty)
directions: Rinse beans in cold water.
Remove broken beans, stones and etc.
Place beans in large bowl with enough cold water over them 3-inches above beans.
Let them soak overnight.
Rinse beans again and put in pressure cooker; add salt, ham hock, V-8 juice and enough water to cover them about 2-inches above beans.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Do not overcook!
(Can be cooked all day in crock-pot.)

title: raisin bread for diabetics
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in a cup of warm water; mix well.
Pour in flour mixture; blend well.
Place dough in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spray top
with vegetable spray.
Cover; let rise until double in size (85° for 1 hour). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil slowly and deeply for top flavor.
Add garlic and cook a few minutes more.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, bay leaf and 2 cups of water.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Add 2 cups water, potatoes, carrots and celery.
Continue cooking until vegetables are done (30 to 45 minutes).
Add beans.
Blend the flour and 1/2 cup water until smooth.
Gradually stir into stew.
Cook a few more minutes, until thickened and bubbly.

title: sweet zucchini relish (or squash)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in kettle and let stand overnight. Drain.
Pour 1 glass of cold water over squash mixture and drain again.
Mix vinegar and pickling spice in saucepan; boil for about 5 minutes.
Strain and pour over sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add to zucchini mixture; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Place in hot, sterilized jars; seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yields 7 pints.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened (DO NOT BEAT). Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured pan.
I use three pans.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables.
Set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and onion salt together.
Put over other ingredients; mix well.
Add bacon just before serving or can be omitted.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Place in glass baking dish and cover.
Freeze until solid.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mushroom-artichoke casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine until tender; drain well.
Combine artichoke hearts, mushrooms, soup, sherry, pepper and Tabasco in bowl; stir well.
Spoon into an 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange julius juice
directions: Put 3 cups juice in blender.
Add other ingredients.
Blend for 1 minute.
Pour into pitcher.
Add the other 3 cups juice and stir.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, cheese, onion and Bisquick.
Put in oiled 2-quart casserole.
Mix eggs and oil. Blend and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole with peas and potatoes
directions: In small bowl, mix milk and soup; mix well.
In casserole dish, layer potatoes, peas, tuna and milk-soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: italian meatloaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper, 1/2 of the tomato sauce, and 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
On waxed paper, pat into rectangle 1/2 inch thick.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Roll up by starting on short side.
Lift paper until meat begins to roll tightly.
Peel back paper to keep it free.
Continue lifting and peeling to complete the roll.
Seal edges and place in a microwaveable loaf dish.

title: classic green chile sauce(serves 8)
directions: Grind vegetables using a coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with towel and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ground vegetables.
Heat to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: monster salad
directions: Predrain fruit.
Mix buttermilk and instant pudding; mix well. Add fruit and mix.
Immediately put into glass dish or plastic bowl (no aluminum).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put Fritos in the bottom.
Add chili, plus onion; top with cheese.
Let cook 30 minutes, or until cheese has melted.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Beat the egg yolks until quite thick. Add the grated rind and juice of the lemons. Mix flour with sugar. Stir into the egg and lemon mixture until smooth. Blend in butter or margarine. Add milk gradually. Beat egg whites until they stand up in glossy peaks. Fold them carefully into the pudding mixture. Pour into casserole or individual custard cups. Set in pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. May be served hot or cold. Makes 6 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes in large bowl.
Add cream cheese in small pieces.
Add butter and beat until melted.
Mix in sour cream. Add eggs to milk, then add to potato mixture with salt to taste. Beat well until light and fluffy.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except soda.
Add shortening, food color, vanilla and 2/3 cup buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add eggs and remaining milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Add to mixture and blend by hand.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Cooked White Icing.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus (keep juice).
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Line baking dish with half the mixture.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes before adding asparagus, at 325°.
Add asparagus; top with remaining mix.
Sprinkle with dry Pepperidge dressing.
Cover well with mild/medium cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or to a toasty brown.

title: rice salad
directions: Add seasoned salt and mix well.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: omelets
directions: Cook bacon and sausage; set aside.
Beat eggs.
Grease a hot skillet with a small amount of Crisco.
Slowly pour the eggs into the skillet.
Let eggs cook completely without stirring.
Add all other ingredients and fold in half.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: tropical ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice; set pineapple aside. In a mixing bowl, combine the pineapple juice and pudding mix; beat on low speed for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Stir in pineapple and 3 tablespoons of the coconut.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Garnish with remaining coconut, cherries and cherry juice if desired.
Chill.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into 2 greased loaf pans or 1 large greased pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: seafood salad
directions: First you take some small pieces of shrimp and lobster; mix them up in a bowl.
Then you get small pieces of clam and mix them up with the lobster and shrimp, then you take the lettuce and cut up into small pieces and get the coleslaw in the salad and mix it.

title: nutty noodle clusters
directions: In
heavy
saucepan, combine chocolate and butterscotch chips. Melt, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir
in chow mein noodles and nuts.
Mix quickly to coat evenly. Dip
out
by
teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 24 Nutty Noodle Clusters.

title: mexican surprise
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of chips.
Cover with ground beef, onions, cheese, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake slowly at 350°.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until well mixed. Refrigerate.

title: beef roast and gravy
directions: Roll roast
in
flour
until
well
coated.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add
roast
and
brown all sides.
Add water, bay leaves and sprinkle in salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Cover, leaving lid open a crack.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 2 hours or until
done.
One
to
2 cups of water may have to be added.
Turn roast
over
several
times before roast is done. Remove
roast from
pot
and
slice.
Return
slices
to gravy mixture in pot; cover and simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and discard before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a baking dish.
Pour in uncooked rice.
Place enough chicken on top of rice to cover. Pour cream of chicken soup and water over all.
Loosely cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar together.
Add sour cream, lemon juice, lemon rind, flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Blend, but do not overbeat.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let shortening soften.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine warm water and yeast.
Let set until yeast is dissolved.
Add eggs.
Combine with other liquid.
Add 3 cups of the flour; mix well.
Add remaining 3 cups of the flour and stir until well mixed.
Cover with plastic wrap and store in refrigerator until well chilled.
Make rolls as desired and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. This dough will keep in the refrigerator for 2 to 4 days.

title: dried beef appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, and mix well.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with chopped walnuts. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve as a spread with crackers.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding according to package instructions.
Add fruit, Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg
yolks.
Blend, then add dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and put in. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add beef and pork; brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, olives, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Add cheese, yellow corn and chili powder.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
(Should be the consistency of baked hash.)
Gradually add one cup corn meal to water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Add one teaspoon salt.
Pour corn meal mixture into greased casserole dish. Add meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Put 2 cups fresh blueberries in cooled pie shell.
Boil remaining ingredients over medium heat until thickened.
Remove form heat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter; cool mixture.
Put mixture over fresh blueberries.
Put pie in refrigerator to set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Combine Crisco, sugars, eggs, vanilla and pudding in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Gradually add flour (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoon, about 3 inches apart, onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: mother's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 350°
oven for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chulies cheese
directions: Mix all the ingredients together with the mayonnaise.
Spread on 8 English muffins; split.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles. If using as an appetizer, cut each muffin into quarters.
If using for a luncheon, leave muffins whole.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients and pour into pie crust; freeze. Serve with chocolate or caramel topping drizzled over top.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Line pie shell with ripe, firm, sliced peaches.
Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and Jell-O until thick and clear.
Pour over peaches; let set until firm.
Top with Cool Whip or a topping you prefer.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not overbake.
Makes 3 small pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches).

title: peggy's cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in a small bowl; let stand until room temperature (softened).
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce. Blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Shape mixture into large ball. Decorate if you wish.
Serve with
your favorite crackers.

title: manicotti
directions: Do not precook manicotti shells.
Mix all ingredients, except shells, sauce and water.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with spaghetti sauce (about 1 1/2 cups).
Fill shells with cheese mixture; place in pan.
Pour the rest of the sauce over manicotti. Pour the water over shells-sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hot spiced apple juice
directions: Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon in spice bag.
Cook in a crock-pot on low heat 2 hours before serving.
Remove spice bag. Serve hot in cups.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: pepped-up cheese bake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together sour cream, mayonnaise, flour and garlic.
Stir in cheese.
Turn into a 7-inch microwave-safe quiche dish.

Microwave, uncovered, on 70% power (Medium-high) 4 to 6 minutes until heated through, stirring twice. Place pimiento in center and sunflower nuts around edge of dish. Sprinkle a ring of onion between pimiento and nuts.
Serve warm. Makes 2 cups.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and two tablespoons sugar.
Add melted butter and the rest of the sugar.
Mix in eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and salt.
Mix well with liquid ingredients.
Let rise two hours.
Stir down.
Don't knead.
Roll out or set in refrigerator.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Make chocolate cake according to directions; let cool. Poke cake full of holes with fork. Cover cake with caramel syrup, then cover with chocolate syrup. Spread Cool Whip, then top the cake with crushed Heath bars.

title: watermelon and noodles
directions: Add a little water and mix until combined.
With floured hands, pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into "cigar" shapes.
Place on floured surface.
Peel potatoes; slice and boil until partially done.
Slice onions.
In frying pan, bring to boil 3/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons Crisco (larger pan, more Crisco). Place noodles in frying pan until bottom of pan is covered (single layer).
Then put a layer of potatoes and a layer of onions.
Cook at medium heat in covered frying pan until noodles are browned on the bottom.
Serve with a slice of watermelon.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Add to melted butter. Combine potatoes, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown meat with bell pepper. Add cooked rice and all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
(You may need to bake it longer as oven temperatures vary.
To be sure the pie is done, check with toothpick in middle of pie until it comes out clean.)
Excellent served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: marseilles lamb burger
directions: Mix all ingredients together (be sure to keep the mixture cold).
Form into 5 ounce patties and broil or barbecue to juicy perfection.
Serve on a multi-grain bun with favorite condiments. Yield:
4 servings.

title: stir-fry broccoli and chicken
directions: Stir-fry onions, meat and broccoli in oil.
Some sticking may occur.
When meat has lost its pink color, add ginger and stir. Add ginger ale and soy sauce.
Cook until sauce reduces a bit, 1 to 5 minutes, leaving vegetables still crisp.
Serve with turmeric rice (cook rice with a sprinkling of turmeric, will color rice). May want to double recipe.
Can be used with beef, venison, pheasant, turkey, etc.

title: mexican egg pockets
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, chives and salt.
In 7 to 8-inch omelet pan or skillet over medium heat, heat butter until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Pour in egg mixture.
As mixture begins to set, gently draw an inverted pancake turner completely across the bottom and sides of pan, forming large soft curds.
Continue until eggs are thickened but still moist.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli or asparagus until tender and put in bottom of casserole.
Cook and bone chicken and place over broccoli.
Make sauce of soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbling and brown.

title: stove top mac-n-cheese
directions: In large pot of boiling salted water, cook macaroni, then drain and return to the pot; melt in the butter. Toss to coat. Whisk together the eggs, milk, hot sauce, salt, pepper and mustard. Stir into the pasta and add the cheese. Over low heat, continue to stir for 3 minutes or until creamy. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil peeled potatoes, whip and add remaining ingredients.
Dot with butter. Do not add milk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix together in large casserole (except sour cream).
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Take out and stir thoroughly.
Cover and bake again 2 1/2 hours.
Stir again.
Add sour cream the last 10 minutes.
(Triple ingredients to serve 10 people.)
Can be used in crock-pot but uncover a while at last to get rid of moisture before adding sour cream.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix all together well and bake at 375°.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Mix wine and soup; pour over.
Cover with stuffing mix; drizzle butter over.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: norma's oatmeal bread
directions: Place rolled oats, butter, molasses and salt in large bowl. Pour boiling water over all.
Let stand until lukewarm. Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add to cool oat mixture.
Blend in flour, a little at a time, beating until dough is stiff, then knead until dough is elastic or bounces back when kneading.
Let rise until double in bulk; punch down.
Make into 2 loaves or 2 dozen rolls.
Let rise again until double.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: killer cookies
directions: Blend well by hand the cake mix, eggs, peanut butter and margarine in a bowl.
Place 2/3 of dough onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press firmly to cover bottom of pan.
In a saucepan at low heat, bring to a simmer the chocolate chips, milk and margarine until melted.
Remove from heat and add the frosting, coconut, pecans and chocolate frosting.
Spread mixture over dough. Crumble remaining dough on top of filling mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: apple bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add other ingredients. Put in greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dale's ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Sauce:
Melt butter; add sugar, poppy seed, salt and mustard. Cook on low heat for 2 minutes.

title: grandma grosskreutz's haystacks
directions: Mix in large bowl the noodles and nuts.
Melt both chips together.
Pour over noodles.
Mix well to coat everything.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and enjoy!

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil, add eggs and mix real good.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add flour with milk a little at a time.
Add nuts, prunes and vanilla. Pour into ungreased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in small pan. Add water and mix.
Heat, stirring so as not to stick. Cook until thick. Remove from stove. Add vanilla and butter.
Mix well. Ready to use. Can be stored in a jar in the refrigerator and reheated in a pan of hot water or microwave.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Spoon into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Boil vinegar, sugar, turmeric and dry mustard for 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mix. Keeps up to 1 to 2 weeks in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-lime punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Pour into gallon jug and fill to top.
Chill until slushy.
When ready to serve, pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: sangria
directions: Combine Burgundy, lemon juice, orange juice and rock candy syrup.
Put soda water in just before serving.

title: pork chop quickie
directions: Place chops in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle generously with garlic salt.
Top each chop with butter and cover with syrup. Add small amount of water to prevent burning.
Bake at 325° until golden brown and tender, about 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind up all vegetables and put into a large bowl.
Mix 1/2 cup of salt and 2 cups of water and pour over vegetables.
Soak in refrigerator overnight.
Mix together vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric and sugar and bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes, put into hot jars and seal tightly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend pudding mix with pineapple and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: zucchini cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in greased dish (9 x 12-inch).
Slice butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: johnny cake chili
directions: Cook ground beef, carrots and onions until all juice is gone and meat is brown.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with juice; add beans, sugar, oregano and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to simmer, uncovered for 20 minutes.
Stir in frozen corn.
Prepare muffin mix as label directs.
Put cheese and olives in ground beef mixture.
Put corn muffin mix into large decorating bag with writing tube and squeeze batter over ground beef mixture in lattice design.
Can use a spoon for batter to create design.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bread is done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with milk to dry ingredients; mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board; add more flour as needed and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut, then dip in melted butter and fold to make pocket book rolls or stack several together.
Place on well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash ripe bananas with a fork.
Stir in sugar, egg, flour, melted butter, baking soda and salt.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: saltine candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Butter tinfoil.
Line cookie sheet with saltines close together.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan. Add next 4 ingredients to butter. Cook and stir on medium to medium high heat until boiling. As soon as it is brought to a boil, continue cooking for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Immediately remove from heat and as quickly as possible, stir in peanut butter and oats. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper to harden.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill at least one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. (Do not overbake.) Makes delicious, soft cookies.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Parboil peas or broccoli until crisp-tender; drain.
Parboil chicken until tender; drain and remove.
Bone and slice over broccoli or peas in rectangular baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Spread over broccoli/peas and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs that have been mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well heated and bubble.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corns, onion, bell pepper and pimento together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole dish (2-quart).

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix well and shape into thin patties.
Fry in very little oil until browned.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
When fresh from oven, pour over 1/4 cup sugar mixed with the juice from the lemon.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage head in a large pot until tender; core cabbage and separate leaves.
Mix hamburger, rice, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Place a handful of hamburger on each cabbage leaf and roll leaf around meat.
Place cabbage rolls in large roaster and top with tomato sauce.
Bake in moderate oven, covered, for about 1 hour, or until tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with veggies or chips.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly. Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and pecans over the first layer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, oleo and vanilla.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening until fine.
Mix eggs with cream.
Combine with flour mixture.
Beat until stretchy.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out circles using a small saucer as a guide.
Fill with fruit that has been cooked, sweetened and cooled overnight.
Wet edges with pastry brush dipped in water.
Fold over filling; press with fork tines around edges.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.
Yields 25 servings.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mash cheese; add pineapple, chopped cherries and marshmallows. Fold the whipped cream and mayonnaise together and add to the other mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: bread dip
directions: Cut top off bread and hollow out loaf. Fill loaf with dip. Place remaining bite size pieces of bread around loaf. Dip may also be used for vegetables.

title: pot pie
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and season.
Cook potatoes and season. Braise onions and sliced hot dogs together.
Make brown gravy. Mix all the ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Make pie crust and roll out to fit on the top of the vegetable mixture.
Bake at 425° until crust is a golden brown.
Make slits in crust for steam to escape.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain cherries.
Reserve 1/3 cup cherry liquid.
Heat liquid. Add cream cheese to melt.
Mix remaining ingredients.
When cream cheese has melted; add to mixture.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: pork sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in pan.
Put sausage and egg into casserole dish. Layer the biscuits on top of mixture.
Put in oven at 350° until biscuits are brown and the eggs are done.

title: fresh tomato soup(slow cooker recipe)
directions: Italian or plum tomatoes ideal, but regular tomatoes can be used.
Drop tomatoes in boiling water 15 to 20 seconds.
Rinse in cold water and remove skins.
Cut in half crosswise.
Squeeze and discard seeds.
Combine in slow cooker with rest of ingredients. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours until veggies are soft.
Puree blender or food processor (can add small amount half and half in last batch for creamier soup).
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip in a bowl.
In another bowl mix milk, pudding and Oreo cookies.
Layer with ingredients in first bowl then second and so on until pot is full. Put gummy worms on top and plant the fake flowers.
Serve someone the "dirt" and they will be surprised!

title: banana brownies
directions: Mix well: flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda; set aside. Place chocolate and 1/4 cup margarine on top of double boiler over hot water; stir until melted and smooth. Remove from heat; cool. In medium bowl, cream remaining 1/4 cup margarine and the sugar until light; beat in egg, milk and bananas. Stir in flour mixture until well blended. Stir in chocolate, leaving mixture slightly marbleized. Turn into greased 9 inch square pan. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven 25-30 minutes. Cover and refrigerate leftovers. Makes 24 (Per brownie: 110 cal. 2 g protein, 16 g carbo, 5 g fat, 11 mg. choles).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain thoroughly.
Stir in butter and egg.
Mix mustard and salt with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk in medium bowl.
Add cheese, reserving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour macaroni into buttered casserole dish.
Add milk/cheese mixture and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° until custard is set and top is crusty, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: perfect rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 225° for 6 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but chips.
Top with chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon in pan you want to make soup in.
Remove bacon and fat.
Add all ingredients except instant potatoes and evaporated milk.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Crumble bacon in.
Add evaporated milk, then add enough instant potatoes to desired thickness.

title: special k cookies
directions: Mix Karo syrup and sugar in saucepan; bring to full boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
