Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well until creamy.
Add Special K cereal, mixing well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper before mixture cools.

title: easy peach shortcake
directions: Spoon peaches over slices of cake.
Top with whipped topping.

title: hot spicy cider
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain spices from cider.
Add orange and lemon juices; stir until heated through. Serve hot.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: hot sausage rolls
directions: Measure flour into mixing bowl.
Cut butter into 1/2-inch size pieces.
Using pastry blender, cut into flour until mixture is in pea-sized pieces.
Stir in cottage cheese until a stiff dough forms.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons ice water if necessary.
Divide into 6 parts.
Roll each part to make a rectangle, 6 inches long and 3 inches wide.
Spread with 1 teaspoon mustard.
Top with a sausage. Roll pastry around sausage, encasing it completely.
Brush with water to seal.
Seal ends.
Place seam-side down on cookie sheet. Prick once or twice with fork to allow steam to escape.
Repeat for remaining sausages.
Mix egg and milk.
Brush pastry coated sausages with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
Arrange on serving tray.
Makes 30.

title: chile with fresh ground turkey
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion and saute.
Drain liquid. In a large kettle over medium heat, add tomato juice and tomato paste.
Add turkey and onions.
Season with chili powder, salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: irish stew
directions: Bring to a boil the following:
corn, green beans, potatoes, onions and garlic.
When it reaches full boil, turn heat down to medium.
Cook uncovered.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll out on a well-floured surface.
Cut noodles.
I use a pizza cutter.
Works great.
Use as needed and store the rest.

title: oatmeal
directions: Bring salt and water to boil.
Add oats and cook 1 minute; stir occasionally.
Cover, remove from heat and serve in 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with milk, butter and sugar.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in a large saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour and mix well with popped corn.
(Pecans, peanuts, walnuts or cashews may be added.)
Bake in a 225° oven for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Store in covered container.

title: chocolate 4 layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together flour, melted butter, pecans and salt; pat into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Crust will not turn brown.
Let cool before adding second layer.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle half of cheese.
Pour remaining mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let cool and thicken.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place unwrapped Kiss on top of cookie.
Press down so that cookie cracks around edge. Remove and cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
When cool, mix with other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt butter in deep 9-inch baking dish. Mix together in another bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk. Add this to butter, but don't stir. Then add fruit on top of this. Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts and pineapple. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 36 large cookies.

title: slow baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
tomatoes
on
a baking sheet, cut
sides
up.
Drizzle on the olive oil and sprinkle with
salt and pepper.
Bake in the preheated oven for 2 to 3 hours
until the
tomatoes
collapse and begin to caramelize. Sprinkle
with the garlic about halfway through the baking and sprinkle with basil just before serving.
Serve hot or at room temperature. This
is
a
sweet
and
savory version of baked tomatoes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, place sugar, pumpkin and oil; mix well.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon, cloves, salt and soda; mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves or 8 baby loaves.

title: dandelion wine(originally from adella smith)
directions: Select fresh flowers and be sure all bitter stems are removed.
Pour boiling water over the flowers and let stand for 3 days.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.

Let stand covered for 3 weeks at room temperature (70-75 degrees) until fermented. Strain into bottles and seal. When first bottled, place wad of cotton in bottle to be sure liquid has finished working.
Takes at least 6 more months to mature.

title: pork braised in white wine with herbs(carne de vinho e alhos)
directions: In a large bowl combine the wine, vinegar, garlic, bay leaf, cloves, savory, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Drop in the pork strips and turn them about until all are well moistened.
Marinate for at least 4 hours at room temperature or 8 hours in the refrigerator, turning the meat over from time to time.
Remove the pork from the marinade and pat it completely dry with paper towels.
Reserve the marinade.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix ingredients in blender until slushy.
Serves 4 tall glasses.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir well until all sugar is dissolved.
Divide into equal portions.
Store in 2 freezer-safe containers and freeze.
Remove frozen punch 3 to 4 hours before using so the mixture is mushy.
Empty the concentrate into large punch bowl and pour one 2 liter bottle of ginger ale over punch.
Do not add ice.
(The frozen slush will do the job.) Repeat with the other container and ginger ale.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Spoon into greased 3 qt. casserole.

title: egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Lightly saute sausage over medium heat; drain.
Layer in order; half each of the bread crumbs, sausage, celery, onions, green pepper and cheese in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Combine eggs, milk, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour evenly over baking dish and spread soup over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour or overnight.
Bake, uncovered for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: This will have to be mixed by hand because of the thick texture.
Put the first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well.
Put dry ingredients in sifter and sift into pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts last.
This is a thick dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onions and bell peppers until soft. Stir in chives, Bac*Os, cheese and biscuits.
Spoon mixture into Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Place Tater Tots in casserole dish. Cover with hamburger and onion. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with a tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir in 1/2 cup sauce.
Combine chicken and cheese.
Add 1/2 cup soup mix.
Place about 1/4 cup chicken mix near center of tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in two shallot buttered casserole dishes (10 x 6 x 13-inch).
Pour remaining soup mix over enchiladas.
Serve with sauce.
Cook at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix juices and other 4 ingredients and thicken with cornstarch (quite thick).
Add to taste celery, cut slantwise, 1 large sliced onion and green pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.
Then add fruit to warm just before serving.
Serve over Chinese noodles or cooked rice.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: One day before serving,
drain pimento and reserve 2 teaspoons pimento.
Mix pimento, artichokes, mayonnaise, green chiles, Monterey Jack and 1/2 cup Parmesan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a greased 1-quart dish.
Top with 1/2 cup stuffing mix. Dot with bits of margarine.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more or until firm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cukes and onion in glass bowl.
Add salt, sugar and dill weed to vinegar and pour over cukes and onion.
Chill 1 hour.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Before	cake is done, cook pineapple and sugar; boil 10 minutes.
Mix vanilla instant pudding as directed.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients all together.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and water.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes with electric mixer.
Add carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts, folding in by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken breasts until almost done.
Remove chicken.
Add bouillon cubes to chicken broth and melt.
Add potatoes and other vegetables and let simmer.
Dice up chicken breasts and add to broth, simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add soup and simmer until thick.

title: aunt nell's taco dip
directions: Begin with the bean dip, spread evenly on the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Mash avocados and spread evenly over the bean dip.
Next spread the sour cream over the avocados. Sprinkle the black olives, then the tomatoes, followed by the onion.
Top with the shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna cream dip
directions: Finely chop tuna.
Mix tuna, horseradish, onion salt, minced onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
For a smoother texture, put mixture in blender for a couple of seconds. Yields about 2 cups.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer on low; blend well.
Pour into large greased tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour 20 minutes.
If using loaf pans begin testing for doneness after 30 minutes.

title: chilli
directions: Cook ground chuck, green pepper and onions all together; then drain.
Add the Cincinnati mix, tomato paste and tomato juice. Cook together, then add tomatoes, beans, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook one hour.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together well.
Use apples and other fruit to dip.
Enjoy.

title: coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, combine cake mix, coconut, pecans, oil, cola and eggs; mix well. Pour batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove cake from pan and let cool completely on rack.
When cool, frost cake with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: marcia's corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and add onion and potatoes to drippings with liquid from corn.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and cream of celery soup.
Heat thoroughly. Crumble bacon on top of chowder just before serving or crumble over individual bowls of chowder.
Serves 6.
Time to prepare: 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese into a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread the refried beans over the cream cheese.
Sprinkle the taco seasoning over the beans.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Serve warm with chips.

title: ground turkey meat loaf(low cholesterol for diabetics)
directions: You can substitute other sauces or mushroom soup (use 1/2 cup or can).

title: summertime pasta with tomatoes and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie cheese, basil, garlic, olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a large serving bowl.
Prepare at last 2 hours in advance and set aside, covered, at room temperature. Boil linguine (1 tablespoon oil and salt in water) until tender, but firm, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain pasta and immediately toss with tomato sauce.
Serve at once, with pepper and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs with milk, then stir in Crisco oil and add combined dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to evenly mix the ingredients. Drop from a tablespoon into heated oil.
Fry about 4 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients into 1 large bowl. Mix with wooden spoon, gently, but thoroughly.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.

title: apple dip
directions: Slice apples and soak in orange juice.
Cream the cream cheese and brown sugar; add vanilla.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pineapple coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Add sour cream.
Stir in drained pineapple by hand.

title: linn's cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 1/4 cup for top.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll dough on cookie sheet.
Pat together perforations. Bake per instructions.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, mayo, dressing and sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Spread veggies.
Pat lightly into cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
(You could top with pimento or black olives.)
Put back in oven for 5 to 8 minutes, until cheese just forms over veggies. Chill, then serve.

title: rolled beef roast
directions: Place roast in slow cooker and sprinkle with soup mix.
Cook at high setting (300°) for 7 to 8 hours for rare; 9 to 10 hours for medium.
Cool slightly for better slicing.
Skim any fat from broth.
Serve warm in broth.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add egg, milk and shortening all at once. Stir in blueberries.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Add milk, crushed wafers, coconut and pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Prepare pastry.
Line a 9-inch Redi Pan deep dish pie pan with pastry.	Flute edges and prick with fork.
Brush
lightly
with egg white.
Bake 10 minutes; cool. Reduce oven to 350°.

title: caramel crumb-top apple pie
directions: Mix flour and 1 tablespoon sugar together and sprinkle on bottom of pie shell.
Place apple slices in shell and pour the cream over them.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and cracker crumbs, flour, salt, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Heat together butter and caramel sauce, stir until well blended and pour over the topping.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for one hour.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until brown. Add water, wine, broccoli spears and soup; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Fluff with fork and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and save the juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Add to Jell-O, mixing well.
Add all other ingredients at same time.
Mix well and chill until Jell-O mixture is set.

title: chicken noodle spinach bake
directions: Drain noodle soup, reserving broth.
Preheat oven to 350°. Dip chicken in reserved soup broth, then coat with bread crumbs. Set aside.

title: rainbow shrimp salad
directions: Split each shrimp lengthwise. Combine shrimp, rice, celery, olives, green pepper, pimiento and onion in large bowl; cover and chill.

title: glazed carrots and rutabaga southern style
directions: Cut vegetables into 2 x 1/2-inch strips or into small chunks. Place in medium saucepan with water.

Cover and cook over medium heat 12 to 15 minutes. In small saucepan, heat butter, brown sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind, dill weed and salt 2 to 3 minutes. Add to vegetables and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer until vegetables are glazed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brandied cherry dessert
directions: Drain cherries, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Cut cherries in half.
Heat brandy and pour over cherries. Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain, reserving brandy.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Add measured liquid and brandy.
Chill until thickened.
Measure 1 3/4 cups of gelatin; blend in whipped topping.
Pour into 6-cup bowl.
Chill until set, but not firm. Add cherries to remaining thickened gelatin.
Spoon into bowl. Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Makes 5 1/2 cups or 10 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, pepper, salt and pepper.
Drain. Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place a layer of meat, then a layer of hash browns; repeat layers.
Spoon soup over the top.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until soup bubbles.
Place cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: thyme-mushroom sauce
directions: In a large skillet cook mushrooms, onion, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper in hot margarine or butter until tender.
Stir together milk and cornstarch; stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add wine; cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Wonderful used as a sauce for Roast Loin Pork.

title: rellenos salsa
directions: Chop olives, green chilies, tomatoes and green onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve with chips or tostados.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook together squash, carrots and onions until tender; drain and mash.
Add margarine, cheese, eggs and crumbled crackers (save enough for top).
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with a little dried parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set.
(Leave cover off.)
Use about a 12 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days. Freezes well.

title: minnesota veal stew
directions: Sprinkle veal with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add veal and cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently until meat is browned.
Add onions, garlic and saffron.
Cook, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to coat meat evenly.
Add wine, tomatoes, broth, rosemary and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 8.

title: kentucky stack cake
directions: Sift
together
dry
ingredients;
set
aside.
Cream together
sugar
and
shortening
until light and fluffy.
Add eggs,
one	at a
time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients
and
buttermilk, alternately to creamed mixture, beating
well
after each addition, starting and ending with
the dry ingredients.
Pour a very small amount of batter into several greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at
325° until done.
Let layers cool.
Stack layers on a cake plate,
spreading cooked dried apples that have been seasoned to taste, between each layer.
Yield: a very large stack cake.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly. Pour into large bowl. Add onion slices and pepper. Combine last 6 ingredients; pour over beans, onions and pepper. Toss gently. Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Drain well to serve.

title: yogurt-jam pops
directions: You will need 12 paper cups and 12 wooden sticks or wooden spoons for this recipe.

title: christmas potato salad
directions: Press into a mold.
Cool.
Remove from mold and top with tomato, green pepper and broccoli, if desired.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown beef and onions together.
Add remaining ingredients, simmer 5 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Melt butter; add milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to milk mixture.
Cook over low heat in saucepan until thick.

title: cucumber hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread mayonnaise on each of the party rye slices.
Top each with a slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with lemon and pepper seasoning salt.
Serve immediately.
Makes 40.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and corn meal together.
Add eggs, butter, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until firm and brown.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour and soda; mix. Add nuts, cherries, chocolate chips and bananas.
Mix well.
Bake in a loaf tin at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: spiced gingerbread
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with wax paper. Butter the paper and dust with flour.

title: merry berry punch
directions: Combine tea mix with ice water.
Add cranberry-apple drink and pineapple juice; chill.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in punch bowl or pitcher.
Garnish with strawberries and lime slices. Pour in the ginger ale.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend until all is smooth (makes about 2 cups).
Leftover dressing can be left in refrigerator.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup milk; cool.
Cream shortening while slowly adding sugar; beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add to batter alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff.
Turn into 2 greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done. When cool, spread cakes with plain whipped cream flavored with 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Combine into layers.

title: lemon bread
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and eggs; beat. Add extract and milk; grate all lemon peel. Set lemon aside. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Grease and flour bread pan. Bake at 325° for 70 minutes. Juice your lemon. Add 1/4 cup sugar.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
and cranberry sauce in hot water.
Add juice (take
juice
from pineapple).
Let cool until thickens. Add pineapple, apple and nuts.

title: glazed acorn squash with walnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Cut squash halves crosswise into 1-inch thick pieces. Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until nearly tender.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix with spoon and bake at 350°.

title: senate bean soup
directions: (Based upon the bone with some meat.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Cover bottom of pie pan with cracker crumbs.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Pour prepared pudding over banana and top with more crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Serve when set.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil sugar and water until it forms a soft ball.
Add dates, chopped.
Watch closely to prevent burning.
Boil 5 minutes longer.
Remove from fire; beat thoroughly.
Shape into a roll. Place in wax paper; chill until firm enough to slice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat mixture before pouring into pie shell.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: syrup custard(grandmother byrd's)
directions: Bake in an unbaked pie crust at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place uncooked Stove Top stuffing bread crumbs in a long shallow baking dish.
Mix season package from Stove Top according to directions on box.
Place chicken over crumbs.
Mix soups and water together.
Combine soup and season mixtures together, then pour over chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar; add zucchini, oil and vanilla. Mix all other ingredients together.
Add both mixtures together; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together melted butter or margarine and cracker crumbs. Reserve some to sprinkle on top.
Combine remaining cracker mixture with broccoli and cheese.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cracker crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.

title: artichoke seafood casserole
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with a hand mixer.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 2 cups rice and set aside.
Cook 2 packages frozen broccoli and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli and rice.
Put in 2 casseroles and bake until hot.

title: sarah's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Alternate adding milk and flour. Mix in lemon and vanilla extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a sprayed 9x13 pan.
Melt 1 stick Oleo or Butter and 1/3 Bag Pepperidge Farm Herb Stuffing Cubes. Sprinkle over Casserole.
Bake 350 for 30 minutes.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix in order given and drop by a teaspoon on cookie sheet. Press down with a fork. Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Bone chicken and dice meat.
Cook spaghetti; season with a small amount of broth.
Add milk to remaining broth.
Make 1 quart.
Add butter and flour.
Heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Saute onion, pepper, mushrooms and celery in mushroom liquid.
Thoroughly blend all ingredients except crumbs in a buttered casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
15 servings.

title: layered dinner
directions: In a greased casserole dish, layer ingredients in order as above:
salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If dish dries during baking, add the tomato juice.

title: pink frozen dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Combine all ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Freeze overnight.
Will keep 3 days.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: taco dip and chips
directions: Mix the cream cheese, taco seasoning and 2 Tbsp. salsa in a bowl.
Spread over the bottom of a large serving platter.
Top with remaining salsa.
Then layer lettuce, tomato, onion and cheddar cheese over salsa.
Serve with chips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add Manwich.
Add your cheese over ground beef and Manwich.
Add potatoes.
Put in oven for 25 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: lee's dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Great with fresh veggies.

title: green beans with pecans and bacon
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to a boil. Add beans; cook 2 to 3 minutes until crisp-tender. Drain in colander; rinse under cold water. Drain (can be done day ahead and refrigerated).

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Roll dough out adding flour to board to make it the right consistency so it won't stick to your cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out when edge is slightly brown.

title: angi's quick pasta and ceci
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil lightly with pepper flakes. Add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Add ceci beans with liquid. Add parsley, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Pour over cooked pasta.
(You may need to add more liquid, water.)

title: deviled crab in the shell
directions: Season to your taste.
Add mayonnaise to mix with ingredients. Fill shell corners with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until delicately brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; let cool and remove from bone and cut in small pieces.
In one pint of broth, cook peppers, onions and celery.
Cook spaghetti in the other broth.
When this is ready, add cut up chicken and other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste and add garlic salt.
Put in a large casserole dish and put grated cheese on top.
This is better to fix and let set overnight.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, baking soda, cinnamon, 1 teaspoon salt, nutmeg and baking powder. Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Fill a pie pan with a raw pie shell and poke holes in it with a fork.
In a double boiler, using a hand mixer or whisk, combine light brown sugar and softened butter (10 seconds in the microwave to soften).
Add granulated sugar, eggs (one at a time), salt, light corn syrup and milk.
Stir over boiling water for 5 minutes. Add 1 cup chopped pecans and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour.
Add 1/4 cup more nuts on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: english monkey
directions: Soak crumbs in scalded milk for a minute or two.
Over low heat, stir in salt and cheese.
Heat and stir until melted. Remove from heat and stir in egg.
Return to heat and stir 1 minute.
Serves 2 or 3.
Good with crackers.
Kids like this for lunch.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 round layers.
When cool, slice each layer in middle, making 4 layers.
Mix instant pudding according to directions.
Fold into pudding one (8-ounce) carton whipped topping.
Drain pineapple.
Slice bananas into juice, then drain.

title: lo-cal cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: sole with tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy based pan and cook onion, celery, chili pepper and spices for 5 minutes over very low heat.
Add red and green peppers and the next 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside while preparing the fish.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients; stir batter until blended.
Sprinkle flour on wax paper.
Pour batter onto flour.
Sprinkle flour over the batter and knead.
Cut out biscuits and place on greased cookie sheet.
Grease top of biscuits with melted Crisco.
Place in oven and bake at 400° until golden brown.
Spread butter over top of biscuits while hot.
Ready to serve.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Preheat over to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour and ice cream, stirring until ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into separate muffin cups.
Bake 13 to 17 minutes or golden brown.

title: praline pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In medium pan, over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Beat in flour, brown sugar, pumpkin, eggs, pumpkin pie spice, vanilla, baking powder, baking soda and salt until smooth.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle praline topping over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Yields 32 (2 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Combine the butter or margarine, orange juice, sugar, cloves and salt in a saucepan.
Cook until butter is melted and the sauce is hot.
Remove the cloves and pour the mixture over the hot carrots, cooked only until crisp-tender.
Garnish with the parsley.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl; add enough water to cover vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Next day, drain.
Add remaining ingredients (in large pan).
Bring to a slow boil over low heat (about 30 minutes).
Put into sterilized jars while hot.
Slow boil in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Boil smoked ham hocks for 10 minutes. Drain and remove skin. Put in large pot with the next 9
ingredients.
Bring to a boil and turn down to a simmer.

Simmer several hours until lentils are cooked, adding water to maintain the level approximately where it was when you began simmering. Just before serving, add salt to taste, cooked macaroni and cut up ham hocks.
Serve with plenty of Parmesan cheese.
Serve 8.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, ketchup, broth, ginger, garlic powder and liquor and pour over chicken in a roasting pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Turn and baste periodically.

title: watermelon pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Divide pudding into 12 pie shells filling halfway up to crust.
Place 5 melon balls on top of pudding.
Pour strawberry glaze over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half the cinnamon-sugar. Repeat with the remaining batter and sugar.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Slowly beat in Cool Whip one large spoon at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Pile in pie shell and decorate with thinly sliced twist of fresh lemon.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend or mix for 15 seconds.
Bake in well-greased 9-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zippy beet dressing("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Mash beets slightly with a fork.
Stir in mayonnaise, horseradish and dash of salt.
Add beet juice if needed to make mixture of desired consistency. Spoon over individual lettuce portions.
Makes enough for 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly:
drain. Add next 5 ingredients and 1/2 c. water, mixing well.
Cook for 5 - 10 min. or until blended.
Layer corn chips, ground beef mixture and cheese, alternately in 9x13 baking dish until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 min. 8 servings.

title: quick n' chicken
directions: Boil noodles as directed on pkg and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place into a large casserole or a 9x13-inch dish. Top with crushed potato chips or buttered crumbs.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Blend together; pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes until golden brown.
Turn off oven, crack oven door and let stand 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Chill. Delicious!

title: ginger carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling water until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.

title: pork chop and rice
directions: Grease pan with butter or cooking oil.
Put rice in bottom of pan.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Pour soup around over top of pork chops and rice.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: sweet and tangy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a well greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle on onion soup mix evenly.
Top each breast with apricot preserves. Uniformly pour Russian dressing over all.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Bake as per directions on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy chicken alfredo
directions: Brown chicken and garlic in oil.
Add artichoke hearts and alfredo sauce.
Heat gently.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Toss with Sauce mixture.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins and water slowly for 10 minutes, then add shortening.
Let cool, then add the sugar, flour, soda, spices and salt.
Beat all together, then add the egg.

title: canned sauerkraut
directions: Shred cabbage; pack firmly but not tight into clean quart jars.
Add 1 teaspoon vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Fill jar up with either hot or cold water; seal tight and set in a cool, dark place, like cellar or basement.
Jars will spume over so you may want to place on papers.
Ready to eat in a few weeks.

title: hummus
directions: Combine drained chickpeas, water, lemon juice, tahini, garlic, salt and paprika.
Beat in electric mixer bowl or food processor until smooth.
Serve with pita bread.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold yolks, then dry ingredients, into egg whites.
Spread evenly on dusted sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
When done, turn out on a moistened and floured paper towel and roll.
When cool, unroll.
Discard towel and fill with desired filling.

title: cherry almond coffee cake
directions: Mix the butter or margarine until creamy.
Add sugar and mix until fluffy.
Mix in baking powder, baking soda, salt, vanilla, almond extract and sour cream.
Add flour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in large boiler; bring to a boil and cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over other ingredients in large bowl and stir until chips and butter are melted.
Pour mixture into flat greased pan.

title: date ball cookies
directions: Cook in saucepan the sugars, margarine, dates and coconut for 6 minutes.
Let cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: saturday special
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion. Microwave 5 minutes on High until beef is set and onion is transparent.
Add sour cream, corn, pimento, salt and pepper. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Top with tomato slices.
Microwave 3 minutes on High or until tomatoes are slightly softened.
Garnish with canned French fried onion rings, if desired.
Let stand 3 minutes, uncovered.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie except stir in chopped nuts before adding water.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and cream.
Stir in vanilla, brandy or flavoring and pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is golden brown.
Cool.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheesy tamale chicken
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Layer the first 5 ingredients.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; fold in yolks, milk and baking mix.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°, or until knife comes out clean.

title: aunt holly's mexican dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a blender until smooth. Pour out onto a serving plate.
Top with lettuce, tomato and olives.
Serve with Doritos.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind the whole orange with the raisins.
Cream sugar and oil. Beat in eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Stir in flour and baking soda. After mixing well, add the orange, raisin mixture.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Mix well.
Mold around olives.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 25.

title: frozen ice cream dessert
directions: Mix cereal, coconut, margarine and honey.
Press 2/3 of mix into ungreased square pan.
Spread ice cream evenly over base. Sprinkle with remaining cereal mixture; press lightly.
Cover and freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Makes 9 squares.

title: grandmother's maple syrup pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; bring to boil.
Add butter to hot mixture.
Mix flour, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Add the hot syrup mixture to the thickening mixture, stirring constantly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°
and cook until the filling is firm.
The egg whites rise and become meringue as the pie bakes. Serve when cool.

title: million dollar pie(yield: 2 pies)
directions: Mix all together, leaving Cool Whip for last.
Put in pie shell with nuts.
Refrigerate for several hours.
May freeze.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute; take off heat and beat until thick.
Spread on cake.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix powdered ingredients together.
Mix milks and vanilla. Mix everything together; cook over medium heat until thick.
Very good served over biscuits....a kid's favorite!

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and vanilla.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve cold with cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken wing-dings
directions: Cut boney tips from wings.
Cut wings in half at joint. Combine dry ingredients and dip chicken in mixture.
Arrange on cookie sheet (one with sides) in a single layer.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sugar plums
directions: Steam dried figs for 1 hour.
Combine syrup, coconut, cherries and almond paste; slit figs lengthwise and fill with this combination.
Roll sugar plums in confectioners sugar.

title: june dairy month punch
directions: Mix in large bowl juices, milk, water and sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Spoon sherbet into bowl and stir lightly.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk and pudding and blend with cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut a circle of waxed paper and line bottom of large flower pot.
Put a layer of Oreos in bottom of pot and then top with layer of filling.
Repeat layers, ending with Oreos.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add artificial flowers and serve with trowel.
Scott likes to add gummy worms!

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Blend together sour cream and soup mix.
Stir in cheese and walnuts.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut butter s'mores(microwave)
directions: For each peanut butter s'more, top one cracker with peanut butter and chocolate chips or candies.
Add marshmallow.
Place on paper towel.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds or until marshmallow is softened.
Cover with second cracker; lightly press together.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Top with slivered almonds.
Cover with crumb mixture made from corn flake crumbs or bread crumbs, mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, stirring until mixture forms a sticky dough.
In a deep skillet, heat 1-inch of cooking oil to 375°.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls a few at a time into hot oil.
Fry until browned.
Drain on paper toweling.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: hot roll mix
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Blend	in eggs and oil.
Add 5 cups Hot Roll Mix.
Blend
well.
Additional Hot Roll
Mix
to make a soft, not
sticky,
dough.
Knead
5 minutes. Lightly butter bowl; put dough in bowl
and
turn to butter top. Cover with damp cloth and let
rise until double. Punch down; divide dough into 24 to 30	balls
of equal size. Place
rolls in a prepared 9 x 13-inch
buttered
pan.
Cover; let rise again until double.
Bake in a
preheated
oven 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy opera fudge
directions: Drain cherries on paper towel.
In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in dry mix and milk.
Stir and let come to a boil for one minute.
Stir constantly and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Beat in XXX sugar until smooth.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Garnish with walnuts.
Chill. Yields 32 pieces.

title: wild apple prune stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Will stuff two grouse, four chukar or two pheasants.

title: sauteed spinach
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Saute onion for 2 minutes. Add spinach and cook until just wilted.
Add raisins and walnuts and toss altogether.

title: pea salad
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, tarragon and nutmeg. Cover the dressing and chill until serving time.
Cook cut up bacon and onions until done, drain off fat.
Mix peas, mushrooms, bacon and onions and chill thoroughly.
At serving time, pour dressing over pea mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: yogurt
directions: Mix milks together; heat on medium to just before boiling. (Top of milk is frothy and steam is rising to the top.) Cool milk mixture to warm (110°).
Mix a cup of milk with yogurt and stir until smooth.
Add to remaining milk mixture.
Mix and blend. Place in quart jars in warm place (110° to 115°) overnight, covered in a cloth (over pilot light of gas stove or in a warm oven).

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; put layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. (Save some for the topping.)
Beat well the oleo, sugar and eggs. Put mixture over wafer crumbs.
Put blueberries over that mixture and press down.
Beat Dream Whip.
Drain pineapple; stir into Dream Whip.
Spread on top of blueberries.
Sprinkle walnuts on Dream Whip; cover top with remaining wafer crumbs and pat down. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl, except pie crust.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour or until brown at 325°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the sugar, syrup and salt in water until it cracks when tested in cold water. Add butter and peanuts.
Cook until golden brown. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda. Stir well.
Pour into well buttered cookie sheet.
Spread brittle out. Chill and break into pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until clear.
Cook all ingredients except bacon and sour cream until potatoes are tender.
Add crumbled bacon and sour cream.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cut chicken as for stewing.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours or until tender in water to which has been added salt, onion, bay leaf and parsley.
When chicken is tender, lift from broth.
Remove bones and shred meat.
Skim chicken stock; score and scrape corn from cobs and add to stock with noodles and cook 10 minutes.
Add chicken and reheat.
Before serving, add finely chopped eggs. Serves 8.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix above together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips or Special K cereal.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves between 12 to 16.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crackers and margarine together and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Place onions in pie plate.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over onions.
Sprinkle pie with freshly grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Melt oleo; let cool.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar, nutmeg and oleo.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cornbread without meal
directions: Mix and cook at 450°.
This is good for people that can't eat cornbread.

title: giblet gravy for dressing
directions: Boil the liver until done and cut in pieces.
Cook onion, pepper and celery in oleo until tender.
Add the milk, eggs, liver and dressing.
Mix and cook slowly for a while.
If too thick, add a little more milk.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar and egg.
Bring water and granulated sugar to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add to sugar and egg mixture. Add Crisco, flavoring and chocolate.
Beat until creamy.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Melt grape jelly and mustard in saucepan over low heat, stirring often.
Add smokies.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Serve hot.

title: bill's barbecue sauce(large recipe)
directions: Cook sauce to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Baste on barbecue food last 10 to 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: blueberry buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine
sifted
flour, soda, salt and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Into a liquid measuring utensil, beat eggs with a
fork; add
buttermilk
and
oil.
Add blueberries to flour mixture
and stir
gently with a fork.
Add liquid mixture to the dry and mix. Do not beat.
Use 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Fry on a hot greased griddle or skillet.
Cook until bubbles
form.
Turn and
cook
other
side.
Yield:
8 to 10 pancakes.

title: toasted almond-cheese sandwich
directions: Set oven control to broil.
Split English muffins; toast. Stir cheese, margarine and marmalade until light and fluffy. Spread about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each muffin half; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon almonds.
Broil until almonds are light brown and mixture is hot and bubbly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: delightful dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, margarine and chopped nuts. Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes and let cool.

title: red, white and bleu slaw salad
directions: Add slaw dressing to cabbage, bacon bits and 1/2 cup Bleu Cheese and toss to combine.
Chill.

title: first place crispy chicken(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Skin chicken.
Put chips and cereal in plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin.
Pour crumbs into a pie plate.
Mix in pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken into beaten egg and milk mixture, then roll each chicken piece in crumb mixture.
Place chicken, meaty side up, in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and beat.
Add lemon juice and mix until thickened.
Put in graham cracker crust and let set before topping with pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: veg-all casserole crunch
directions: Mix and pour into 9x13 inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange bran muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Pour water, margarine and sugar in blender and blend.
Add milk in 1/3's and blend after each 1/3.
Pour in a jar.
Keeps 3 to 4 weeks.

title: foolish pie(1953 recipe)
directions: Beat egg whites to partial froth and add salt and cream of tartar.
Continue beating until mixture holds shape.
Add 1 cup of sugar, all at once.
Beat until mixture holds shape.
Then add 1 cup of sugar, gradually, beating slightly.
Add vanilla. Pour in a large baking sheet with greased brown bag at bottom.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Should be dry and crisp.
Cut into 24 squares and serve with strawberries and whipped cream or bitter-sweet chocolate.

title: taco dip
directions: Let the cream cheese come to room temperature.
Combine with sour cream, taco seasoning, onion and green pepper.
Spread in a shallow dish.
Top with tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut 1/4-inch from each end.
Slit cucumber lengthwise into 4 pieces.
Pack into 1 gallon large mouth containers, ends up.
Don't overpack.
Put in dill, garlic, water and vinegar until almost full.
Take out some liquid and dissolve salt.
Put back into jar.
Let stand in sunlight 6 to 8 hours. Chill and eat.
Must be kept in refrigerator.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer slowly for 1/2 hour.
Use with any kind of meat; especially good with corned beef.
Yield: about 5 cups.

title: sweet sesame seed braids
directions: Work butter and sugar until light in color.
Add 1 egg at a time, then vanilla.
Mix baking powder with flour.
Add to other mixture, gradually, and mix and knead until dough can be rolled into rope-like strand.
Cut into lengths; shape into wreaths or braids.
Brush tops with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes a dozen.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Blend together first three ingredients with fork.
Add lard. Mix until crumbly.
Then in small bowl, mix water, eggs and vinegar.
Pour into flour mixture and mix until moist.
Makes 6 crusts.

title: texas chicken and rice
directions: In large frying pan, saute onions, peppers, tomatoes and garlic in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken.
Stir in bouillon and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until rice is tender.
Serve with tortilla chips and picante sauce.
Serves two or three.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix.
Add sugar to taste.
Add large ginger ale before serving.

title: fruit ambrosia parfait
directions: Combine fruit and chill.
Fold coconut into whipped milk. Arrange alternate layers of fruit mixture and whipped cream in parfait glasses.
Garnish with additional coconut and whole strawberries.

title: chicken romon
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned coating mix as directed on package and arrange in single layer in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, combine cheese, bacon, mayonnaise and peppers, blending well.
Spread over baked chicken and broil for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 X 13 pan. pour pineapple over pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix on top. Drop pieces of oleo on top of cake mix, Bake until cake is done. Serve with cool whip.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, mix 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and set aside. Peel apples and cut into thin slices; set aside. In a large bowl, beat eggs until thickened. Add 2 cups sugar and oil to egg mixture; mix well. Resift flour (using soup strainer) with baking powder in a large bowl. Add flour and baking powder to egg mixture alternating with vanilla extract and orange juice, ending with flour mixture. Pour about 1/4 batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Add cinnamon-sugar mixture to sliced apples, toss to coat apples. Place 1/3 of apples on top of batter. Continue to add more batter and apples, ending with batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes, checking to ensure it's baked through. May need to bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes if necessary. Batter may be slightly moist when done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in baking dish, greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring it occasionally, until done.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Boil turkey heart, liver and gizzard for 1/2 hour, cool and grind in meat grinder.
Also, grind the carrots and onion and store in separate containers in refrigerator until ready to stuff turkey.
Then, mix all ingredients together and loosely stuff turkey.
Yields 12 cups.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Combine 2 tbs. melted butter, spices, and sliced peaches with juice. Stir cornstarch and water together. Mix into peach mixture. In another bowl mix milk, sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt. Melt 1/2 cup butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour batter over melted butter. Spoon peaches over batter. Mix together the sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Clean, devein and butterfly shrimp.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch greased dish.
Crush Ritz crackers; place over top of shrimp. Melt butter; sprinkle over top of crackers.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until shrimp are opaque.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine by hand all the ingredients and form into medium size balls. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies will start to crack on top when finished. Do not overcook. Allow to cool 15 minutes.

title: double fudge chocolate pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Melt butter and 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir milk, vanilla to taste and chocolate mixture into first mixture.
Pour into deep pan.
Loaf pan can be used.

title: autumn cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish and cover with 1 can of Comstock cherry pie filling.
Add 1 cup sherry wine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be made ahead and reheated.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart well-greased casserole, evenly layer potatoes, meat, carrot and celery.
Top with pepper rings and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a little shredded cheese.
Cook and cover for 2 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an uncooked deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean (at times I have cooked pie for 1 hour).
May be poured into 2 smaller pie crusts and cooking time adjusted accordingly.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Boil all the ingredients until the water is gone (high heat), stirring constantly.
Put in shallow baking pan in 250° oven. Bake for 1 hour or until desired doneness.
Stir about every 15 minutes.

title: butter apricot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs. Add oil, brown sugar, apricots and cake mix.
Pour batter into a greased tube pan. Bake 45 minutes until done. Cool right side up for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, salt and rice to a boil, stirring frequently. Lower gas to simmer.
Cover and cook 1 hour and 15 minutes. After 1 hour and 10 minutes, slowly pour in sugar (stirring, not to stick to pot), egg at room temperature and, finally, the vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Thoroughly blend sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together dry ingredients and gradually add to mixture.
Stir in grated carrots and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch pans or two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf.
Place on a rack in a shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: nellie delk's "burnt sugar cake"
directions: Burn one-half cup sugar in iron skillet to a deep brown, add water, shake well until all sugar is dissolved and set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly, add egg yolks that have been beaten until thick and lemon colored.
Add milk and mix flour sifted three times with baking powder and soda.
Then add burnt sugar liquid and lastly the beaten egg whites and flavoring. Bake in layers at 350° until done.
Cover with Caramel Frosting.

title: hot apple decadence
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions. Meanwhile in a 2-quart saucepan, combine pie filling, raisins, pecans, orange peel and cinnamon.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Scoop ice cream into shells; top with apple mixture.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vanilla, oil, sugar, egg whites and skim milk.
Sift together baking soda, flours, cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini to the first mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Shake quartered biscuits in cinnamon mixture to coat.
Place in lightly greased Bundt pan.

title: deviled egg dip
directions: Chop egg yolks and mix with all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Mix in butter and raisins.
Mix sour milk and eggs together and pour into flour and knead.
Form into a round and mark with a cross.
Put in hot skillet and bake in oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss to coat evenly with dressing.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During the last 15 minutes put shredded cheese on top and melt.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Mix in a large stainless steel pan.
Add ground vegetables to mixture and cook for 3 minutes.
Can in clean pint jars.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: chipped beef hors d'oeuvres
directions: Put in 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes.
Dip or use knife and spread on Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: brains (pork)
directions: Wash and clean brains.
Beat with mixer.
Add baking powder, salt, pepper and milk to brains.
Mix with mixer.
Add flour to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Brown one side, then turn over, flatten with spatula and brown on other side.
Yields 6 to 8 sandwiches.

title: paula's three layer salad
directions: Cook until thick.
When cool, spread on top of Dream Whip and cream cheese topping. Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: blueberry-sour cream corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium-sized muffin cups or line with paper liners; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Add combined egg, sour cream and apple juice concentrate; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool slightly.
Combine cream cheese and fruit spread; serve with warm muffins.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Coat chicken with flour; reserve remaining flour.
In skillet over high heat in hot oil, brown chicken.
Remove from skillet. Into hot oil, stir onions and remaining flour.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in bouillon, paprika, salt and pepper and 1 1/2 cups water. Add chicken; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until tender, turning once.

title: beef and rice
directions: Cook beef and soup very slowly, about 2 to
3 hours; when done, add cooked rice and simmer 5 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tin with cooking spray. Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine bananas, applesauce, orange juice and egg.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients; stir until smooth.
Spoon into muffin pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Place margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk in large saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Melt butter.
Combine eggs, butter, mashed bananas, flavoring and water.
Add cake mix and blend.
Beat for about 4 minutes. Bake in a 10-inch greased tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Can be baked in 2 small pans.

title: special mozzarella chicken
directions: Dip 4 chicken breasts in flour, then into beaten eggs, then into seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in butter and remove from skillet.
Place chicken breasts flat in baking dish and sprinkle with garlic salt.
On each piece of chicken, put one piece of cooked ham.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Pour sweet cream over chicken.
Top with enough fresh chopped parsley to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: potato and hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season.
Combine vegetable soups and 1/3 can water.
Alternate layers of potatoes, soup mixture and hamburger in greased casserole.
Repeat until all are used.
Blend mushroom soup and 1/3 can water.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: no-peek skillet chicken
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium high; brown chicken. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic.
Combine with soup mix.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: prime rib
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Using
an
open roasting pan, place prime rib in pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Gently rub with olive oil.
When oven has been completely preheated, cook roast 5 minutes per
pound.
When meat has cooked the allotted time, turn oven off.
Leave
the
meat in the oven to rest for at least 2 hours.
It can
wait
up
to
4 hours.
Do not open oven doors from the time
you
put meat in until you are ready to serve. Meat will be rare and juicy.

title: two bean salad
directions: Heat beans thoroughly and add sugar.
Chill onion, oil and vinegar.
Shake well and pour over beans.
Rechill before serving.

title: pink cake
directions: Cut cake in half crosswise to make 2 layers.
Draw syrup from strawberries into top of double boiler.
Sprinkle in the gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add to berries.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold into the cream which has been whipped and sweetened with the sugar.
Fill and frost the cake.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: apple haroset
directions: Place the apples and walnuts in a food processor and pulse until fairly finely chopped.
Transfer to a bowl and stir in red wine, honey and cinnamon.
Serve chilled or at room temperature. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
The Apple Haroset can be refrigerated, covered, for up to 6 hours.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix in a medium bowl margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Take the party rolls out of the tin tray as a whole piece (do not tear them apart); cut through the center of the bread vertically so that you have a top and a bottom.
Place the bottom of the bread back into the tray.
Spread the butter mixture evenly on each bottom.
Then sprinkle the ham over the margarine and then the cheese over the ham.
Replace the top of bread.
Lightly press down on the top to make sure secure.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, salt, butter and milk for 6 minutes and stir as it melts.
Pour over the chocolate and marshmallow cream. Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.
Let stand several hours and cut. Store in tins.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: almond tea
directions: Dissolve tea in hot water.
Combine sugar and 2 cups cold water and boil for 5 minutes.
Add tea mixture, lemonade and extracts. Heat thoroughly.
Add 8 cups cold water and mix well.
Makes 3 quarts.
Serve hot or iced.

title: baxley fire dept. chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can be filled with filling.
Press thumbprint and fill. Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Layer chicken in greased casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup broth and soups; whisk together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix 1 cup broth, stuffing mix and butter.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mary's dessert-salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries.
Stir until jello begins to thicken.
Add sliced bananas.

title: party beef log
directions: Mix together well cream cheese, beef and Worcestershire sauce. Add finely grated green onions.
Mix well.
Form into 2 logs and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Roll logs in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Can be made several days ahead of use.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: sourdough pancakes(crepe-style)
directions: The night before:
In 2-quart mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water, then gradually mix in flour.
Set in warm place overnight (i.e. in oven, warmed to 90°, turned off and door left closed). The next morning, mix in remaining ingredients.
Batter should be thin after mixed.
Best if cooked on electric griddle at 295° to 300° at the table! Don't make ahead.
Maple syrup time!

title: herb butter turkey
directions: Mix over stove until blended.
Pour over turkey breast.
Put in a 325° oven and cook for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put tinfoil over breast when cooking.

title: vegetable beef chowder
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add chili powder, if you like.

title: clara's oriental mushroom soup
directions: Heat broth, water and soy sauce in large saucepan.
Add carrots, celery and onions; cook 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms, spinach; reduce heat and simmer covered about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with clear plastic wrap. Pour cereal into large bowl.
In saucepan, combine corn syrup and sugar.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Pour over cereal and quickly stir.
Press into prepared pan.
Cool at least 15 minutes.
Invert pan onto cutting board.
Remove plastic wrap and cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cherry cheese brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Slice fruit; mix in bowl.
Sprinkle with grated coconut.

title: favorite cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to come to room temperature.
Add garlic powder or garlic salt and combine.
Add nuts and mix well.
Make sure cheeses are mixed well and pecans are evenly distributed.
Shape into ball or log and roll in chili powder.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add 1 egg at a time to sugar mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in pumpkin and water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and dice potatoes.
Combine potatoes with cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix the first 5 ingredients.
Then stir in grated carrot, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
In a separate bowl beat eggs, salad oil and vanilla.
Stir this mixture into flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling to the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 14.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix lemonade according to directions on can.
Mix together all liquids.
Add sherbet when ready to serve.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Chop or grind vegetables.
Place in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt. Allow to stand overnight.
Drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and cayenne pepper.
Add spices tied loosely in a thin cloth.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Pour at once in jars; seal.

title: creamed chicken and cornbread
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken and save broth.
Cut chicken into bite-sized chunks.
Melt margarine over medium heat in large skillet.
Add cornstarch, stirring constantly.
Add milk all at once, stir and add 1 cup broth. Stirring constantly, until thickened, add salt, pepper and chicken.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve over cornbread.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Dip veal first in seasoned flour, then in beaten egg and lastly in fresh bread crumbs.
Pat firmly to make a neat coating. Fry in hot butter, turning often to brown evenly, until golden brown.
Take about 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve very hot.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into a small casserole dish. Top casserole with crushed Ritz crackers sprinkled with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tenderloin deer steak
directions: Slice the deer tenderloin crosswise into steaks and pound well.
Place in a bowl and cover with milk.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain and sprinkle with salt to taste.
Dredge with flour.
Fry in small amount of shortening until lightly browned and serve hot.

title: brown rice and pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil.
Drain.
In a medium boiler, melt butter; add rice, stirring constantly.
Cook rice until it starts to brown.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add beef consomme.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: friendship bread
directions: Day 1:
Do nothing on day you make or receive mixture.
Stir well with wooden spoon once a day.
Day 5:
Put in large bowl with lid.
Stir well.
Add to mixture 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 cup milk.
Stir well.
Do not refrigerate!
Repeat Day 5. Stir and put 1 cup of mixture into 3 small containers.
Keep one, give other 2 to friends.
(The 3 cups of mixture in containers are starters and are already on Day 1.)
To remaining batch, add above ingredients on Day 5 and pour into two well-greased and sugared (powder) loaf pans or 1 bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, salt and 3/4 cup half and half in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Do not boil.
Combine cornstarch and remaining 1/4 cup half and half.
Gradually stir into brown sugar mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Stir in vanilla.
Yields 2 cups.

title: goro
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add cream, melted butter, then sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll out thin and cut out, using paper pattern to fit Goro iron.
Place on heated iron; turn to bake other side.
After removing from iron, cut in thirds while still warm.
Store in an airtight container or a dry area.
Keep rest of dough chilled while rolling out individual pieces.

title: homemade dressing
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients until mixed.
Cook until thick on cool.
Add mustard and salad dressing or mayonnaise.

title: january casserole
directions: Combine in a large 3-quart covered baking dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks lightly.
Add sugar, flour and butter.
Add milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites (not stiff).
Add vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and sprinkle nutmeg over top lightly. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then reduce to 250°. Bake until done, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: raisin rusks(cookies from russia)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large baking sheet.
Place 3/4 cup raisins and 1/2 cup flour in food processor, and pulse until raisins are coarsely ground.
In large mixing bowl, stir together chopped raisins with remaining 2 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in oblong baking dish. (Less margarine can be used to suit your own taste.)
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: dream pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat topping mix with 1 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix. Blend at low speed, then high speed for 2 minutes. Spoon into pie shell and cool for 4 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix pepper, salt, sugar, vinegar, salad oil and water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Set aside to cool.
Pour liquid over the combined vegetables.
Let this sit in the refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain the pineapple well.
Mix with shredded carrots and raisins.
(To plump raisins, let them sit in warm water for 10 minutes and drain.)
Add walnut pieces.
Moisten with a little mayonnaise.
Chill before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well all the ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Recipe doubles well for large gatherings. This is a very light dessert.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook
vinegar,	sugar,	margarine and milk to soft ball stage. Pour
candy mixture over peanut butter and marshmallow cream and beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: tabbouleh(middle east)
directions: Wash burghul; drain water.
Cut very fine the parsley, cucumber, green onions and green pepper; mix with the burghul.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix salt, mustard, onion and half of vinegar.
Add other ingredients alternately.
Add celery seed last.
Chill.

title: gooey squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Pour 1/3 cup of the cream cheese mixture over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle 1/3 cup powdered sugar mix over top. Cool and cut into squares.

title: garden relish
directions: Cut corn off raw.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and salt.
Mix together with the vegetables and cook for 1 hour. A big kettle makes one batch.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Put apples in water with cinnamon and sugar.
Cook until tender.
Mix flour, lard and milk.
Roll out crust 1/8-inch thick. Cut in rectangles and place 1 tablespoon of apples in center. Fold and crease edges.
Fry in melted butter.

title: low-fat sour cream enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Cut chicken, onion and green pepper into strips. Saute with Pam.
Sprinkle with enchilada seasoning.
In a medium bowl, combine sour cream, yogurt, soup and chilies.
Mix well. Sprinkle a small amount of cheese in tortilla and spread about 3 tablespoons sour cream mixture down the center of each tortilla along with chicken mixture.
Roll up and place in baking dish. Cover with salsa and remaining sour cream mixture.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Remove foil.
Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake and filling
directions: Sift
dry ingredients.	Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add all together and cook for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan over low heat or microwave in suitable container.
Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate bits and butter or margarine.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill until firm. Cut into small squares.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: oven baked crab dip
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Gently stir in crabmeat.
Put in buttered 1-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers. Yield:
2 3/4 cups.

title: sour cream cheese cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream until smooth.
Mix in cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Pour into crumbs crust and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 35 minutes or until set in the center.
Turn off heat and leave in oven for 15 minutes. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: oven "fried" fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to very hot (475°).
Spray a nonstick cookie sheet or shallow baking pan liberally with cooking spray or wipe with vegetable oil.
Combine yogurt, oil and juice in a shallow dish; mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on wax paper.
Dip fillets in the yogurt mixture, then press into the crumbs, lightly coating both sides.
Arrange fish in a single layer on the cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika, if using.
