Bake fish, uncovered, in preheated very hot oven (475°) for 8 minutes.
Do not turn fillets.
Fish is done when coating is golden and fish flakes easily.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage in baking dish.
Chop onion on top of cabbage. Pour melted butter over cabbage and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, mushroom soup and egg.
Pour on top of cabbage and onions.
Shred 1 cup cheese on top of this.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts. Blend well at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch bread pans, which have been greased on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss gently.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Contains 36 calories per serving and low-fat.

title: gloria's chocolate-vanilla dessert
directions: Mix pudding mixes with
1/2 cups milk.
Stir in Cool Whip. Butter 9 x
13-inch
dish.
Layer 1 package of crackers in bottom of dish.
Add
one-half of pudding mixture.
Layer 1 package of crackers
and
rest of pudding.
Layer last package of crackers. Remove
foil
seal
from icing and microwave for approximately one minute.
Pour
over
top
layer of crackers. Chill.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Work together with hands until well mixed.
Use 1/2 cup mixture for each egg and shape.
Chill for 2 hours on wax paper.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Use tongs to dip eggs in chocolate.

title: grilled salmon fillets
directions: Squeeze fresh lemon over each fillet.
Rub or brush olive oil over both sides of fillets.
Season well with lemon pepper, dill weed and tarragon.
Grill approximately 4 to 5 minutes on each side (depending on size of fillets) or until fish is cooked throughout.
Serves 2.

title: cherry homemade ice cream
directions: Whip the eggs well.
Add condensed milk, sugar, vanilla and skim evaporated milk.
Beat well and pour into ice cream freezer container.
Add half and half.
In blender, put the maraschino cherries (juice too) and blend just a few seconds.
Pour into freezer container with remaining ingredients.
Fill to fill line on freezer with whole milk and freeze.

title: lobster thermidor("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and spices.
Stir in hot milk over low heat.
When sauce thickens, stir in cheese and cream until melted.
Add lobster.
Put in oven to heat through.
Place under broiler with bread crumbs on top and broil until golden. (Be careful not to burn.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray with Pam one 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1/2 minute or until well blended.
Scrape sides and bottom; pour into pan(s).
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Slice when cool.
Freezes well.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in large pot on low heat.
Then add onions. Saute for 10 minutes.
Add water, cream of mushroom soup and Rotel tomatoes.
Stir and mix well.
Then add crawfish tails.
Add seasonings, cover and cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In a large saucepan, combine margarine and onion.
Saute until the onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Transfer mixture to a large slow cooker and cook over low heat until cheese is melted, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Makes 10 cups.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Chop peaches into shell; set aside.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook in saucepan until thick and clear.
Stir in package of Jell-O (peach).
Pour over peaches in shell.
Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, more or less Miracle Whip to taste. Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cheese.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: caramel pecan nut bars
directions: Melt
caramels
and 1/3 cup milk in double boiler.
Add butter, mix and 1/3 cup milk.
Spread 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips over cake.
Pour caramel over cake, making sure you
get
the edges covered.
Pinch off remaining batter and put over
the
cake.
Sprinkle
1/2 cup of nuts and press down.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Stir all together until well coated.
Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy pan.
Cook for 3 minutes, no longer.
After mixture comes to a full boil, add oatmeal and vanilla.
May add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: simple pecan pie
directions: Combine the ingredients all together.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour in a slow oven at about 300°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all.
Let stand a few hours before serving.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, mayo and dry Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Unroll crescent roll dough and place on cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together and lightly press dough to cover bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Sprinkle on shredded cheese and small florets of broccoli and/or cauliflower and other vegetables.
Cut into squares.

title: maw maw's pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in dry mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Use 1/4 cup dough for each cookie.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Spread into pumpkin shape.
Add a bit more dough for stem.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from sheet.
Cool.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops and place in large shallow pan.
Prepare stuffing from recipe on package; shape and form dressing on each pork chop.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tortilla chicken and dumplings
directions: After chicken is skinned and deboned, cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
Mix soups in chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Drop tortilla pieces into mixture at a rolling boil. Cook until brown spots come off tortillas. Stir to prevent sticking. When tortillas are done, salt and pepper chicken and add to mixture.

title: seasoned corn meal for fish or chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.

title: chicken breasts with mustard sauce
directions: Sprinkle the chicken breast halves with salt and pepper.
Heat the butter in a skillet and add breasts.
Cook until browned (approximately 6 minutes).
Turn the pieces and cook another 6 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake in a covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and heat slowly.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: festive mashed potatoes
directions: Mash
potatoes.
Add
sour
cream,
butter
and
cream cheese.
Combine eggs, onion and milk.
Add to potato mixture. Mix well and put into a greased 9-inch casserole.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and press together into 2 small or 1 large ball. Roll in chopped pecans. Great with any cracker.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Mix sugar and cream cheese. Beat Milnot until whipped stiff; add all together with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour mixture over graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Make a big pan, don't need to add anything to grahams.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: micro peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Make a hole in the center and add butter and milk.
Don't stir!
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Quickly add crunchy peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well by hand.
Roll into balls and place on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: black-eyed peas in sauce
directions: Soak peas 1 hour.
Boil meat 30 minutes in enough water to cover.
Add spices. Add tomato puree. Cover and let boil slowly 3 to 4 hours or until done.
Serve with rice and tasty cole slaw or vegetable salad and corn sticks.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and flour until smooth.
Chill about 2 hours.
Press into muffin tins.
Beat together brown sugar, egg, butter and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Put 1 teaspoon filling in each tart.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 dozen.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Add margarine, cocoa, water and oil; bring to boil.
Add 2 cups sugar and 2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
When cool, spread with the icing.

title: grilled lobsters with herb butter
directions: Preheat grill until very hot.
Place lobsters, flesh side up, on preheated grill.
Melt the butter.
Crush the garlic with the salt.
Add to the butter along with the oregano and rosemary. Brush the lobster flesh with the Herb Butter.
Grill 10 minutes. Brush again with melted butter mixture and turn lobsters, flesh side down.
Grill 3 to 5 minutes more, or until meat is just done. Serve lobsters, flesh side up, on a large platter with the remaining butter spooned over them.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chop suey
directions: Sear (but not brown) the meat.
Add water just to cover.
Add celery and cook slowly until celery is soft.
Add thickening and the rest before heating to serve.

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Mix jello by package directions.
Let this partly set.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Fold into the chilled jello. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out on large cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix until creamy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle on fresh vegetables.
Top with dill seasoning.
Cut into squares.

title: hash brown zucchini patties
directions: Mix zucchini with salt.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Squeeze with hands to press out moisture.
Stir beaten eggs into zucchini. Add cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Combine well.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Saute until golden brown, turning once (about 4 minutes each side).

title: pizza primavera
directions: Spread shell with sauce, leaving a 1/2-inch rim around edge. Carefully layer the veggies, except for the sliced tomatoes. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place Mozzarella over top (be generous).
Place tomato slices on top of this.
Starting with outer ring and working inward, sprinkle with seasonings and bake in oven according to package directions.
Cheese should be melted and veggies tender.
Enjoy.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip mufkies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough into greased muffin pans. Fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: one skillet spicy chicken 'n rice
directions: Combine flour and seasoned salt in plastic bag.
Add chicken. Shake to coat well.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil. Continue cooking, uncovered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is cooked through.

title: orange cinnamon loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Place in bowl the milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, then yeast and 1/2 of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour gradually and knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise to double.
Divide in half.
Roll out to 1/2-inch.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar and cinnamon mixer on each half. Roll each like jelly roll.
Place in bread loaf pan.
Let rise. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sesame seed salad
directions: Toast together in a skillet almonds and sesame seeds.
Add to lettuce and bacon.
Set overnight.
To make dressing, mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper together and set in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, shake dressing and pour over salad. You can add chopped boiled eggs, mushrooms or cheese if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Make into walnut size balls.
Mash flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain vinegar off dills and discard.
Cut pickles in chunks and put back in jar.
Add all other ingredients.
Let stay out of refrigerator and shake until sugar dissolves.
Shake often.
In 24 hours you have a crisp, sweet pickle.
Refrigerate after sugar is dissolved.

title: microwave lemon squares
directions: Mix the graham crackers, brown sugar and melted margarine. Firmly press 2/3 of the mixture into 8-inch square microwave dish. Stir together the condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add the milk mixture and spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top.
Pat down gently.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, rotating dish after 4 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: mickie's hot hominy
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole dish with cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp and spinach pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Line two 13 x 9-inch baking dishes with pasta.
Saute shrimp in butter for 5 minutes. Cover pasta with shrimp. Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, chives, mustard and sherry.
Pour sauce over shrimp and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: panettone
directions: Make a "well" or "volcano" with the flour.
Melt butter; let cool a little.
Add yeast, salt, butter and a little lukewarm water to the well.
Adding water as needed, integrate ingredients until most of the flour is absorbed.
Knead until soft but springy.
Cover with cloth; let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down dough; let rise for another 45 minutes.

title: billie's mock champagne
directions: Mix ginger ale, apple juice and raspberries.
To ornate the punch, float a frozen heart-shaped mold made from raspberries. (Pack raspberries firmly in mold, then freeze.)

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces.
Place in shallow baking pan. Combine all ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours basting several times.

title: beer nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer until all liquid is absorbed.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at
300° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: greek casserole
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Mix in cinnamon, tomato paste and salt.
Set aside.
Work flour into the salad dressing and gradually stir into the milk.
Cook and stir until smooth and thick.
Don't boil.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs with cheese and nutmeg; stir into milk sauce.
Add drained macaroni to the sauce and spoon half of this mix into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with meat mixture and top with remaining macaroni and sauce.
Bake at 325° until set and brown, about 45 minutes.
Allow to set a few minutes before cutting into squares.

title: uncle clayborne's caramel cake filling
directions: Mix and cook to soft ball stage.
Cool, then beat until spreadable.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in milk, cream and broth.
Cook and stir until mixture is slightly thickened and bubbly; reduce heat.
Stir in chicken and pepper; heat through.
Garnish with snipped chives and parsley, if desired.

title: cheese custard
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt, crumbs and cheese.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a buttered dish.
Place baking dish in a pan of water and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, or until a knife inserted in custard comes out clean.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix together carrots, oil and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: chicken-duck dressing
directions: Boil 2 ducks until tender with 2 apples (with seeds taken out).
Debone duck after done.
In separate pan, boil 1 fryer until tender and debone.
Mix duck and chicken broths together with meat.
Mix 1 large skillet of cornbread; bake.
Let cool and then crumble.
Mix all ingredients together until mixture is slightly "soupy."
If need more broth, you can use 1 can cream of chicken soup or small amount of milk.
Pour in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spanish chocolate
directions: Melt the milk chocolate bars in the cream over low heat, stirring constantly. Stir in the coffee and beat with a rotary beater to a heavy froth.
Serve hot with a dab of whipped cream or pour over crushed ice and top with whipped cream.
Yields four (5 ounce) servings.

title: raspberry mold salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water in blender.
Blend in blender the cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: tender-rich buttermilk biscuits
directions: Set out a baking sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together into a bowl.
Cut lard in with a pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Pour buttermilk in all at one time.
Stir with a fork until dough follows fork. Gently form dough into a ball and put on a lightly floured surface. Knead lightly with fingertips 10 to 15 times.
Gently roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured cutter or knife.
Place biscuits on sheet and bake at 350°.

title: lo-cal chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Arrange in casserole dish.
Stir all ingredients together.
Spoon over the chicken.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain.
Saute minced onion and pepper with sausage.
Mix with other ingredients and chill.
Serve with Doritos.

title: melva's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in mixer.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Slowly add flour.
Stir in by hand the oatmeal and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: diabetic cranberry-orange relish
directions: Wash and sort berries.
Remove seeds from oranges.
Put both through the fine blade of a food chopper.
Blend in sweetener. Chill well before serving.
Makes 8 servings, 22 calories or 1/2 diabetic fruit exchange.

title: fruit juice jelly
directions: In an 8 to 10-quart kettle, combine juice, pectin and lemon juice.
Bring to a full rolling boil (a boil that cannot be stirred down).
Stir in sugar.
Return to a full rolling boil.

title: bits of brickle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, softened butter and egg.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle evenly Bits 'o Brickle and chopped pecans over the mixture.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top of the mixture evenly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Slice into bars to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Combine all ingredients except bacon in greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir well; top with bacon slices.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crunchy pie crust
directions: Combine ingredients; press into place in a 9-inch pie plate. Fill with favorite pie filling.

title: grandpa karie's corn bread
directions: Put meal in bowl.
Add egg and melted butter.
Add buttermilk to make batter a little soupy.
Pour into an 8-inch greased iron skillet.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: green chili
directions: Put meat in large pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (until meat looks done, no longer pink).
Remove lid and cook juice away.
Serve on flour or corn tortillas with your favorite taco toppings.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Add whipped topping, folding until smooth.
Spread over crumb crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator. Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: caviar-cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave, then beat with fork until smooth. Stir in mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and hot sauce. Blend well. Spoon onto serving tray and shape into low, flat mound.
Mix mashed eggs and parsley. Cover cream cheese mound with mixture, pressing it gently in the mound.
Top with layer of caviar and serve with crackers.

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add sherbet.
Mix until sherbet is melted and jello will be thickened.
Add Cool Whip and mix with electric mixer.
Add oranges, place in shallow dish and refrigerate.

title: simple turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place in a loaf pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Pour an 8 ounce size can tomato sauce over turkey mixture.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Yields 10 servings.
Per serving: 0.7 g fat, 112 calories (6 % calories from fat) and 27 mg cholesterol.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Add milk and margarine and mix together.
(Batter will be thin.)
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and spread with peanut butter. Refrigerate to set.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut
off
and
discard the small tip of each wing.
Cut the main
wing
bone and second wing bone at joint.
Sprinkle with salt,
if
desired,
and
pepper to taste.
Heat oil in a deep fat fryer
or
large roaster.
When it is quite hot, add half
of the
wings and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until
golden brown and crisp.
Remove; drain well. Repeat with remaining wings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and then add milk and egg yolks and stir constantly until thick.
Then add butter and mix well. Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat at medium speed until creamed.
Add cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add flour to creamed mixture, then eggs. Do 4 times, ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Check, may need a little longer.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat eggs and add milk together. Roll out 20 crackers and add to egg and milk mixture. Add corn and mix well. Put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, margarine, shortening and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour and baking powder gradually and milk to mix. Mix into dough ball and chill.
Roll out thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Roll out on floured surface.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a preheated 425° oven.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk; mix.
Pour in pan and then add fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use any kind of fruit.

title: cider tapioca
directions: Mix and let stand
5 to 10 minutes before cooking.
Sometimes I add lemon rind or, for a different texture, add a grated or chopped apple and then cook.
Good warm or cold.
Excellent with cream.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Add all ingredients; simmer 1 hour, covered.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve hot or cold.
Best if cooked one day ahead.

title: spicy baked fish fillets
directions: Combine flour and mustard in small mixing bowl; gradually stir in milk.
Add tomato, parsley flakes and salt.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Place one layer of fish in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon half the tomato mixture over fish.
Top with remaining fish and tomato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes when pierced with fork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate peanut butter dream cookies
directions: Beat sugar, peanut butter and butter until fluffy.
Blend in water, eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: rouladen
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions in reserved drippings until tender.
Remove onions from skillet.
On each steak, spread mustard. Top with 1 slice of bacon, about 1/2 cup onions and 1 pickle spear.
Roll up.
Secure with wooden picks. Coat with flour.
In the same skillet, brown meat in oil. Add 1 1/3 cups water, bouillon, thyme and bay leaf, bringing to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove meat from skillet and bay leaf.
Mix remaining 2 tablespoons water and 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into liquid in skillet. Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Remove picks.
Serve meat and gravy with noodles.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: the best fudge
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients, one at a time in order.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bean and bacon casserole
directions: Cut bacon
into
pieces.
Chop
onion and cook in bacon until translucent, but not crisp.
Add next four ingredients. Cook until heated and bubbling.
Put remaining ingredients in shallow 2 quart
dish.
Pour
first mixture over top and mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Make topping.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix the crackers, melted oleo and sugar; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix together the pudding, soft ice cream and milk; beat until thick.
Pour pudding mixture on top of crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Spread 1/2 cup crumbs on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and press in buttered pan.
Freeze 2 hours.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Melt the chocolate chips with the paraffin.
Dip squares.
Let cool.

title: saturday bean soup
directions: Drain the soaked beans, rinse and put in a crock pot with the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook for 5-6 hours on high. Lower the temperature, remove the bay leaf and the soup is ready for the day.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Mix beef, chili peppers and onion with 1 can sauce.
Wrap this mixture in tortillas.
Pour a little sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place enchiladas in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over them and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients and place in greased 2-quart casserole; bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Top with potato chips.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mixed fruit jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add juice and water to make 1 cup cold water.
Chill jello until firm.
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix with pineapple.
Beat jello; add Cool Whip, then add cream cheese and pineapple.

title: carrot banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate carrots; put aside.
Process bananas and margarine in food processor about 20 seconds.
Add other ingredients, except carrots and nuts.
Process 10 seconds. Scrape sides of bowl and stir in carrots and nuts.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 50 to 60 minutes or when tested with toothpick.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: lois' hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables with coarse blade. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Have in crock or enamel container.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain well. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture; then heat to boiling and simmer 3 minutes. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put in buttered baking dish as listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is tender.
I cover it and take cover off a short time before it is done.

title: barbecued beef
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, mix water and all other ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Cook mixture, covered over medium-low heat, about 50 minutes, or until steak is fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: milkless, butterless, eggless cake
directions: Boil in saucepan for 3 minutes sugar, water, shortening, raisins, spices and salt.
Cool.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Combine and bake in tube pan, greased and floured, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: rice custard
directions: Add the milk and rice slowly and heat with egg yolks, sugar and salt in a double boiler.
Beat the egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice and spoon over top.
Bake in oven at 425° until delicately brown (about 5 minutes).
Serve from the baking dish.
Meringue is best if served within an hour.
The pudding can be made ahead of time and meringue added just before ready to serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add cornstarch to evaporated milk in a cup to break lumps down.
Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until thick.
Beat in sugar.
Combine melted butter with flour, cocoa, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Add to egg mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven. Spread on marshmallow cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in refrigerator overnight and remove 1 hour before baking. Top with buttered bread crumbs or potato chips. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake according to package.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake bakes, put pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil gently until it thickens a little, about 5 minutes. When cake is baked, immediately pour pineapple mixture over cake. Make up vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Cool cake.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Blend mustard and vinegar in glass dish and let rest for 30 minutes. Add sugar and beaten egg.
Cook in double boiler 1/2 hour until thick. Stir often. Serve warm or cold. Store, covered, in refrigerator; it will keep indefinitely.
It's great on sandwiches, hard-cooked eggs or as a dip for salami or cheese pieces.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in 2 pie crusts (not baked), then bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: olympic seoul chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together vinegar, soy sauce, honey and ginger; set aside.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut can of biscuits (10) in half, making 20 halves.
Peel apples and quarter.
Wrap 1/2 biscuit around each of the 20 pieces and lay in baking dish (9 x 13-inch) with smooth side up.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; add cup of sugar and cup of water.
Pour over apples.
(Will seem watery.)
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; reduce to 350° and cook 15 to 20 minutes more.
Remove and sprinkle mixture of sugar and spices over apples.
I drizzle the juice over the apples before sprinkling mixture.
Delicious.

title: mary grilc's phyllo dough strukle
directions: On a towel, lay 6 sheets of phyllo dough.
Melt butter and brush all over, but not on each layer.

title: lemon ice
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring water, sugar and lemon zest to boil; boil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes, then stir lemon juice into sugar-water.
Pour into freezer trays and freeze 1 1/2 hours or until icy.
Stir and break up ice crystals with a fork.
Freeze again until firm, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: beef oriental casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in uncovered skillet at 325°.
Remove any excess grease.
Add cooked macaroni, water chestnuts, pimento, celery soup, milk and soy sauce; stir to blend.
Bring just to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Reduce to "warm" setting and garnish with chow mein noodles for serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit nibblers
directions: Scoop balls from melons or cut melons into 1-inch cubes. Place 3 balls on each of 12 bamboo skewers.
Insert skewers in oranges on a serving plate.
Serve orange juice in tiny bowls for dipping melon balls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix well, roll in balls, dip in water then in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down if you like.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place rice, onion soup mix, water and soups in dish.
Mix until moist.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Cover and let bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: grasshopper cake
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in the pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and frost when cool.
The following glaze works well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour water over dates; let stand until lukewarm.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla flavoring.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and pour into mixture.
Add nuts and dates with water to the flour mixtures.
Stir and pour into pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: cinnamon-chocolate squares(delicious with coffee)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Add margarine, whole egg and egg yolk. Blend well on low speed. Turn into greased 11 x 7 x 3/4-inch pan. Spread evenly with back of a spoon. Beat egg white slightly. Brush white over mixture with a pastry brush. Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, chocolate pieces and nuts. Sprinkle over top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares. Makes 3 dozen.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Cook onions until tender; drain liquid, about 1 1/2 cups. Thicken with flour, cut in cheese and bring to a boil; simmer until cheese has dissolved. Pour over onions and put in 2-quart baking dish, covered with buttered bread cubes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "no mess" microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Put popped corn in brown paper sack.
Put sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a 6-cup bowl.
Cook 4 minutes on High (stir after 2 minutes).
Remove.
Add soda and stir together ingredients.
Pour on top of popcorn and shake bag.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes; shake.
Cook 45 seconds; shake.
Cook 30 seconds; shake.
Let cool.
